title: red hot cinnamon apples
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Bring other ingredients to boil.
Add apples; cook gently until apples are tender.
Hot fruit cans very well.
Pack into hot jars and process in boiling water bath as you do applesauce, 15 to 20 minutes.
(Oil of cinnamon can be purchased at the drugstore.)

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Add to chicken mixture.
Stir and mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Combine breadcrumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 3-quart baking dish.
Combine Veg-All homestyle mixed vegetables, tomatoes, onion, green pepper, lemon juice, basil and oregano in a bowl.
Pour over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: twist casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on box.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Mix in barbecue sauce and onion.
Heat. Layer half of the dinner in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spoon on beef mixture.
Top with rest of the dinner.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange julius (fruit frosty)
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend until ice is crushed. Should be thick.

title: mexican candy
directions: Add sugars, cream and Karo; cook until forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, vanilla and butter. Mix well.
Add pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in tight container.

title: mexican pork chops with beans and corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a large size 14 x 20-inch Reynolds oven cooking bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add salsa, lime juice, chili powder and garlic powder in bag. Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place pork chops in bag.
Spoon beans, corn and peppers around pork chops.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Cut 6 1/2-inch slits on top.
Bake until chops are tender for 1 1/2 hours.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: twenty-minute cassoulet
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.

Reserve 1/2 teaspoon drippings in a large saucepan and add celery, onion, garlic, thyme and rosemary. Cook and stir 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add cooked sausage and remaining ingredients except green onions. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top each serving with sliced green onions.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with seasonings until done.
Use just enough water to cover chicken.
Water can be added as needed.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs and milk together and add to shortening mixture.
Add dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Gently fold in berries and bake in a greased pan until golden.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft and slightly browned. Sprinkle with flour.
Stir and cook over low heat 3 to 4 minutes. Pour in beef stock and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Season with salt and pepper as desired.
Simmer about 20 minutes. Add Worcestershire or A.1. sauce.
Place thick slices of French bread in ovenproof bowls, pour in soup and top with cheese.
Brown under broiler.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: $100.00 fudge
directions: Put butter or margarine, marshmallow cream, chocolate chips and vanilla into a large bowl; allow to come to room temperature. In a large pan combine sugar and milk. Bring to a boil stirring constantly and boil for 10 minutes. Add to the first mixture and blend well. Pour into a greased pan and refrigerate. Makes about three pounds.

title: sweet potato casserole #2
directions: Mix above ingredients and place in buttered casserole.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix 4 cups sugar with 6 cups water and heat until dissolved. Add to juices.
Blend bananas with about 1/2 cup of juice.
Then add blended bananas to juice.
Freeze mixture.
When ready to use, pour ginger ale over frozen mixture.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add dry ingredients.
Combine applesauce and soda. Add to mixture. Stir in the milk. Add nuts and raisins.
Use a 7 x 11-inch baking pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon, drain and crumble. Cook beef in fat, add onion and saute until tender. Combine beef mixture with catsup, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar in a 3 quart baking dish. Partially drain all the beans, add to baking dish, sprinkle with bacon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn-broccoli bake
directions: *Can substitute Mrs. Dash's all natural seasoning (1 teaspoon).

title: deviled eggs
directions: Mix ingredients in egg yolks and sprinkle with paprika. Refrigerate until served. Recipe may be doubled.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and garlic until onions are tender.
Add milk, yogurt and soup mix.
Stir constantly.
Add seasonings and cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat. Oil a casserole dish.
Add cauliflower.
Pour sauce over all. Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes. Uncover and bake until golden brown, 10 minutes.

title: jessica's chocolate pie
directions: Soften Cool Whip and divide evenly into 2 medium bowls. Add 1 box of Jell-O to each bowl. Add 3/4 cup milk to each bowl and blend well. Empty devil's food bowl into graham cracker crust. Smooth white chocolate mix over that. Refrigerate until firm, about 1 to 2 hours. Serves 8. May be it can be frozen. Must do ahead.

title: freezer pickles(2 days)
directions: Refrigerate the first 3 ingredients for 24 hours in covered bowl.
On the second day, drain and add the sugar and white vinegar.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate 24 hours.
Put in desired size containers and freeze.
Makes 2 quarts of a good sweet pickle. Can be halved if you have only a few cucumbers.

title: potato boats with beef
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper in skillet.
Drain off fat. Add seasonings and tomato sauce. Cut potatoes in half length wise. Scoop out and reserve shell.
Mash the potato, combine with meat mixture.
Put into potato shells and place in baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 4 - 8 servings, depending on size of potatoes. May be prepared in your microwave.

title: mother's original rich shortcake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add combined milk and egg.
Turn out on slightly floured surface.
Divide dough in half.
Pat out to fit 8-inch round pans.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.
Fill with any fruit.

title: banana salad
directions: Make jello, let set until shaky then add drained pineapple (save some juice), bananas & marshmallows. Put in large dish in refrigerator, chill till firm. Take leftover pineapple juice add enough water to make 1 cup combine egg, sugar & cornstarch cook till thick. Set aside till cool, add cool whip - fold together & pour over top of fruit then spread shredded cheese on top. (I use red jello for Christmas.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 24 hours. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo, margarine and vanilla flavor. Beat all this together, then add crushed nuts. Pour in pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, cover with 1 cup grated cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and egg yolks in heavy saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Grate the two lemons.
Stir in rind and juice. Add butter.
Cool and pour into cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: chicken curry
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add curry powder and stir in flour. Cook 2 to 3 minutes, then add chopped garlic and green pepper. (Mixture will be very thick.)
Add chicken broth and evaporated milk.
Simmer slowly until thickened (about 15 to 20 minutes). Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add chicken.
Serve over rice.
Suggested condiments:
chopped eggs, bacon bits and peanuts.
Sauce without the chicken added freezes well.

title: quick ham stroganoff
directions: Cook ham and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in mushrooms and soup.
Cook 5 minutes.
Just before serving, blend in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve on rice, eggbread or noodles.
It looks pretty to put chopped parsley in the rice.
Yields 5 servings.

title: mushrooms berkeleyhouston, texas
directions: Saute onion in butter using a fry pan.
While onions are cooking, use a blender to mix the mustard, Worchester sauce and sugar. To this paste, add the wine along with lots of pepper and a little salt and blend.
Back at the stove, add the mushrooms and peppers to the onions and saute on medium heat.
Stir often.
As mushrooms brown and shrink, add the wine sauce.
Be careful not to carmelize while simmering.
(Does not reheat well for the same reason).
Simmer at least one hour or until you can stand it no longer.
Looks horrible, tastes great!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook slowly onion in butter until tender; add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: tomato salad
directions: Add garlic powder, pepper, salt and parsley to taste.
Add wine, vinegar and oil.
Mix well and chill.

title: mama's dressing
directions: May use fresh ham, chicken or turkey.
Cook celery, pepper and onion together for juice.
Mix all ingredients together and add juice with cooked vegetables.
Bake at 250° for one hour.
Recipe may be doubled for larger pan of dressing.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender 10 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Mix sugar, sour cream and 1 1/2 packages of frozen coconut.
Do not cook, just stir well.
Pour on cake (still in pan) and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup coconut.

title: zack's casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Combine margarine and stuffing mix.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: honey-mustard glazed sausage kabobs
directions: Prepare grill for Direct Method.
Assemble each kabob using 4 pieces of meat and 3 to 4 pieces of each vegetable on 4 (12-inch) skewers.
Combine honey, mustard, oil and vinegar.
Place kabobs on grill rack over medium heat.
Brush half of the honey-mustard glaze over kabobs.
Grill 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn kabobs and brush with remaining glaze.
Continue grilling 4 to 5 minutes or until hot. Makes 4 kabobs.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar, then beat in the eggs (one at a time).
After that, mix the rest of the ingredients.
When the mixture is well mixed, pour it into 2 small loaf pans.
Keep it in your oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until it is done.

title: english muffin bread(for bread machine)
directions: Add in order as listed to the bread machine.
Use white bread setting.
Do not worry if the top of this bread sinks.
It is okay.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: You will need a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch greased cookie sheet.

title: glazed onions and carrots
directions: Place carrots in large saucepan with 1-inch boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until vegetables are just tender.
Drain; return vegetables to saucepan.
Add butter, brown sugar, ginger and salt. Stirring frequently, cook over medium-high heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are glazed.

title: no fail dumplings
directions: Cook a hen or fryer until tender.
Make sure you have at least 3 quarts of broth or more.
While this is cooking, make your dough for dumplings.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cut steak into serving size pieces; dredge in flour mixture.
In a skillet, brown steak in oil.
Drain and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with celery, onion and mushrooms.
Combine water, garlic and steak sauce.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and bacon in a casserole dish.
Mix all together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach and mushroom lasagna(serves 8)
directions: Bring a large pot of well salted water to a boil and prepare a large bowl of ice water. Add the lasagna noodles to the boiling water and cook until they are just al dente. Drain and plunge the noodles into the ice water to cool them quickly. Drain again and lay the noodles out on paper towels.

title: joan eckersell's barley casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add barley and put in a casserole dish.
Add mushrooms, almonds, soup mix and chicken broth.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients ready; it cooks fast!

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well in the center. Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients. Stir quickly until dry ingredients are blended.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana split
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick margarine and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 2 sticks margarine and sugar; beat hard for 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs. Slice bananas over mixture.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Put nuts and cherries on top.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers (washed and pared)
thinly into a bowl. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix and set aside for 1 hour.
Squeeze cucumber slices, a few at a time (discarding liquid) and put into a bowl.
Pour vinegar mixture (vinegar, water and sugar and seasonings) over cucumbers and toss lightly.
Chill salad in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.

title: donna's mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: peanutty bars
directions: Combine cake mix and next 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes. Press 1/2 of cake mix mixture into bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips and drizzle with condensed milk.
Sprinkle with remaining cake mix mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yield: 24 bars.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Make pudding with the milk.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers with the pudding mixture.
Top with chocolate frosting. Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in large bowl.
Combine Crisco, margarine, water and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil. Pour over flour; mix and beat well.
Mix in milk, eggs, vanilla, soda and cinnamon.
Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim excessive fat from chops, render in frying pan.
Turn heat to medium-high and brown chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper and place in baking dish.
(Use a deep baking dish.)
To the baked beans, add chili sauce, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over chops and place green pepper rings over top.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Use a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: fresh corn cakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg.
Add milk, corn and shortening.
Add to flour mixture and mix well. Cook on greased hot griddle.

title: pineapple meat loaf
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Add 1 tablespoon catsup to reserved juice, mixing well.
Set aside. Combine drained pineapple, remaining 2 tablespoons of catsup and next 6 ingredients.
Shape into an 8 x 5-inch loaf on rack in broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; remove from oven and brush with reserve pineapple juice mixture.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until done.

title: one-pot pork chop supper
directions: Brown chops; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.

title: dessert crepe batter
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Slowly add flour and sugar alternately with milk and water.
Then beat with a whisk or electric mixer until smooth. Beat in melted butter. Chill batter at least 1 hour. Cook in a crepe pan.
Makes 20 to 25 cups.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all in large casserole and cover. Bake 5 hours at 250° or longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt 1/2 stick butter with Velveeta cheese in broccoli.
Stir to mix.
Crush 1/4 pound or 1 sleeve Ritz crackers and add 1/2 stick melted butter.
Place in a buttered casserole and sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until cheese bubbles through crackers and turns brown.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt margarine.
In separate pan, mix sugar, flour and cocoa. Pour into margarine.
Mix well.
Add eggs one at a time and stir after each one.
Add milk and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: momma lu's sticky chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with celery salt, garlic salt, salt, pepper, Accent, flour and paprika to season, then place in roasting pan and dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°.
Turn chicken and pour 1 cup boiling water around chicken.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Baste often for another 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shark, shrimp and fish batter
directions: Wash and cut shark in thumb size pieces.
Shrimp are left whole and fish to your size.
Soak in beer mixture.
Mix together cornmeal and flour.
Add Konriko Hot and Spicy Creole Seasoning to your taste (about 4 tablespoons should do it).
No extra salt is needed.
Roll fish in dry mixture and deep fry.
Don't overfry for this will make them dry.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and set aside.
Preheat to 325°.
Cream soft butter and sugar together.
Add one egg at a time beating well after each egg.
Add flour and baking powder a little at a time.
When all flour mixture is added, beat well. Add 7-Up and lemon extract a little at a time until it is all added.
Beat for 3 to 4 minutes on medium high speed.
Bake in a bundt pan greased with Crisco and sprinkled with sugar.
Bake for 1 hour, or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Beat butter or margarine, peanut butter and sugars; blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine oats, flour, soda and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugar.
Gradually cream with shortening until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs and bananas to mix thoroughly.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans in a 350° oven for 65 minutes.

title: chicken croissant
directions: Pull chicken off bones.
Place on wide end of croissant and roll up to small end.
Bend ends and place in casserole dish.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Process cabbage, onion, carrots and celery in food processor until coarsely shredded.
Toss vegetables in salad bowl.
Mix sugar, salt, vinegar and oil in small bowl.
Pour over vegetables, toss lightly.
Chill in refrigerator.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: country style pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for one hour or until peas are soft.
Remove ham hocks.
Put the pea mixture through a sieve or in a blender for a few minutes.
Cook over low heat until heated.
Makes 6 cups.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven and bring to boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes; uncover and simmer an additional 20 minutes.
Strain and discard spices.
Serve hot. Yields 3 quarts.

title: chinese pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add butter and sugar.
Add vinegar, syrup, coconut, chips and pecans.
Put in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: peach pickle salad
directions: Pour the 2 cups boiling water over lemon jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add to hot jello one package of plain gelatin, dissolved in 2 tablespoons water.
Drain peaches and pineapple. Measure juice and add enough water to make 4 cups.
Add the juice to jello.
Cut the peaches and pineapple into pieces.
Add to jello.
Add pecans.
Peel and shred the apples
on large side of grater.
Add to jello.
Congeal.
Serves 16.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let sit overnight.
Stir in 2 quarts of water.
Serve hot or cold.

title: crazy macaroni
directions: Follow macaroni box instructions.
Boil cut-up hot dogs.
When macaroni is done, drain and add hot dogs and tomatoes.
Heat until warm.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, eggs, sugar and molasses together until smooth.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Stir well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan fizz
directions: In 3-quart pitcher, prepare limeade concentrate as directed. Measure 1 cup reconstituted limeade into 1-quart saucepan; over high heat, heat to boiling.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in peach gelatin into hot limeade, stirring until the gelatin completely dissolves.
Stir mixture into limeade in pitcher.
Place half the peaches and their syrup in blender; blend at high speed until pureed.
Repeat with remaining peaches and syrup.
Stir puree and lime juice into limeade mixture.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until well chilled.
To serve, stir in tonic water into limeade mixture.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Melt butter in pan you can mix all in (may be melted in microwave).
Cool slightly.
Stir in brown sugar, unbeaten eggs, vanilla and nuts. Stir in dry ingredients.
Spread in a greased 11 1/2 x 17-inch pan (do not use smaller pan).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut at once.
Freezes very well.

title: bisquick turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, turkey and vegetables. Pour this into a 9-inch pie plate that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Spread in well-greased casserole the frozen potatoes.
Layer sausage over potatoes.
Add a layer of the cheese.
Beat the eggs, 2 1/2 cups of milk and mustard with salt.
Pour over cheese.
Mix the soup and 1/2 cup of milk and sliced mushrooms.
Layer over eggs.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or just overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: eggplant sandwiches(this is an "all day" process.  the end result is delightful!)
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/8 inch slices; drain.
Dip eggplant into beaten eggs and fry in a hot skillet with small amount of oil or margarine until lightly brown (1 to 2 minutes per side).
Again dip the eggplant slices into the eggs; coat with bread crumbs and fry lightly again.
In a casserole, spoon a layer of spaghetti sauce, then a layer of eggplant, continuing until the remaining spaghetti sauce is poured on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with 3 or 4 slices on a roll.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Put a layer of sliced potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle chopped onion and place sliced cheese over them with a little salt and pepper.
Repeat layer.

title: vegetable beef soup(slow cooker)
directions: Cover and cook on low for 12 hours.
Thick and delicious.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo. Add oil and eggs; mix well. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with glass that has been dipped in sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Makes 13 to 14 dozen small cookies.

title: breakfast pita pockets
directions: Preheat toaster oven to 350°.
In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except pitas and stir to blend.
Fill each pita half with 1/4 of the peanut butter mixture.
Wrap each pita half in foil and bake until heated through, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate cracker sandwich cookies
directions: Spread about 1 teaspoon peanut butter on each of 30 crackers; top with remaining crackers to form a sandwich.
Heat frosting in a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, just until melted (do not overcook).
Using 2 forks, dip each cracker sandwich into frosting, coating completely.
Place on waxed paper. Let dry uncovered for 8 hours.
Store loosely covered.

title: easy brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add rice and stir over medium heat until brown. Slowly add bouillon and salt.
Cover and cook slowly 25 minutes until rice is tender, adding water if needed.

title: pepper-herb mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Shake before using to blend.
Yields about 1/3 cup.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Combine the 1/3 cup sugar and the teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll biscuits in sugar mixture, then put biscuits in a Bundt pan, well-greased.
Bring the butter, 1/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon to boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal pecan cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and eggs. Sift together salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour. Mix all ingredients together and drop by rounded tablespoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes; watch closely.

title: little angel clouds
directions: Mix cake flour, confectioners sugar, pecans or walnuts, butter and vanilla.
Shape into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pillsbury's country apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg at low speed until crumbly.
Press in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan; spread with pie filling.
Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
In small bowl, blend sour cream, 1 egg and vanilla.
Pour over sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden.
Serve warm or cool.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Yields 12 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Mix al other ingredients together, except Cheddar cheese.
Pour in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and spoon cornbread on top.
Bake at 375° until cornbread browns.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain and mash sweet potatoes. Add melted oleo and sugar to sweet potatoes and mix until oleo and sugar are dissolved. Add salt, vanilla, milk and eggs and mix well.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with the following topping.

title: crystal's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch pie shells; use 2 regular 9-inch pie shells, not deep dish shells.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in microwave-proof bowl or 4-quart measure.
Gradually add hot water and lemon juice.
Cook, stopping to stir, until smooth and thickened.
Stir in blueberries and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove from microwave.
Stir in butter until melted.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream, cake or cheese cake.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Wash and core peppers and cook about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, mix ground beef, rice, onion, tomato sauce, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Pile mixture into drained peppers and arrange in casserole.
(Peppers may be halved if desired.)
Bake covered in 350° oven about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 10 minutes more to brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix margarine with stuffing mix.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl. Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: In oven going Dutch oven, fry chicken in oil with onion and garlic.
When done, add tomatoes and water.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add bay leaf, salt, rice, saffron and green pepper.
Stir thoroughly and place in moderately hot oven for 20 minutes. Garnish with petits pois and pimientos.

title: onions au gratin
directions: Slice onions and arrange in baking dish, overlapping slices. Pour broth over onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry lettuce salad
directions: Mix oil, white wine, sugar, mustard and poppy seed; refrigerate.
Drizzle dressing over salad before serving.

title: black forest brownies a la mode
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
With an electric mixer, beat until blended the brownie mix, 1 cup filling, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until brownies spring back when touched.
If desired, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand until softened.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place meat, vinegar and water to cover roast and seasonings in a bowl.
Marinate 3 days (turning daily).
Remove roast to Dutch oven and brown.
Add carrots, onions and 1 cup marinade.
Cook 4 hours in a 350° oven.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Add sugar and crumbled gingersnaps to liquid.
Cook until thickened.
Add more vinegar, salt and pepper, if desired.
Spoon some gravy over meat. Serve the rest separately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Mix all together and simmer.
Do not let it boil.
This amount makes a crock-pot full.

title: bacon wrapped prunes
directions: Cut bacon into 3-inch lengths.
Remove pits from prunes.
Wrap each prune with bacon strips.
Secure with toothpick.
Broil until bacon is cooked, turning once.
Serve immediately.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese in separate bowl.
Spread mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crush corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Pour soup and milk into 2-quart casserole. Stir in chicken, vegetables and thyme.
Place biscuits over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple pizza
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and pat dough onto a pizza pan or baking sheet.
Crimp edges as for a pizza.
Spread apples over dough and sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Dot with butter and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan cheese spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put 1 teaspoon on crackers (wheat type crackers or cocktail rye bread seem the most tasty); slide under broiler to brown.

title: miniature mounds
directions: Mix and chill.
Make small balls and dip in chocolate.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add oil. Stir well and add eggs. Add carrots and lastly the nuts. Grease and flour three 8 or 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 325° to 350° for about 40 minutes. (Batter may seem a little thin, but will be OK.)

title: potato onion casserole
directions: Alternate potatoes and onions in layers in a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Add salt and pepper to each layer.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over layers. Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onions in shortening.
Add tomatoes, garlic, bay leaves, oregano, cumin, salt, chili powder, sugar and pepper. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add water if chili gets too thick during cooking.
Add parsley 30 minutes before chili is ready.
Mix flour with cold water or tomato juice to form a paste and add to chili to thicken.
Stir thoroughly.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water, add marshmallows and 2 cups cold water.
Stir until cool.
Drain pineapple to save juice. Add pineapple and bananas to gelatin.
Let set until firm.

title: halifax pudding
directions: In a saucepan, bring brown sugar, butter and boiling water to a boil again. Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, sugar, raisins, milk and vanilla.
Drop into the middle of the former mixture and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes its own sauce.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, milk, butter and eggs.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: barbecue
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients well, then add the meat and simmer 2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat mushroom soup, milk and Cheez Whiz just enough to melt cheese.
Pour over potatoes in buttered casserole dish. Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: wednesday night special
directions: Cover hot dogs with water.
Boil until swollen.

title: mrs. doll kirkley's fruit cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and spices 4 times.
Set aside, then cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar to butter and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Roll fruits and nuts in flour and spices.
Add fruits, nuts and flour into batter.
Then add jelly, syrup and cider or wine.
Mix thoroughly and pour into four 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pans lined with heavy paper.
Grease paper lining too. Bake at 250° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Makes 10 pounds fruit cake.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Wash, peel and devein shrimp.
If large, cut in half crosswise.
Cook onion, pepper and garlic in margarine until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Crush tomatoes and add. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blue ribbon apple crumb pie
directions: Pare apples; core and cut in eighths.
Arrange in unbaked pastry shell.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain off juices and save.
Combine pudding and juices.
Cook and cool.
When cool, add fruit and bananas and mix.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy, adding milk, if necessary.
Put in a buttered dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt syrup, sugar and salt together but do not boil.
Take off heat, add peanut butter, corn flakes and Rice Krispies.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with icing.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients in an ungreased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes, covered, and then 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: baked scallops with mushrooms
directions: Clean scallops; wash and slice mushrooms.
Melt 2 teaspoons of butter and saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix berries with sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Pour in filling and cover with pie crust.
Bake in a very hot 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Note:
If using plain all-purpose flour, add 1 teaspoon salt and 3 teaspoons baking powder.

title: sweet and sour sauerkraut
directions: Crumble sausage in a large skillet; brown sausage.
Do not drain.
Add silver sauerkraut and brown sugar; mix well and simmer on low for about 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven and skillet in oven at 400°.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in skillet before you put skillet in oven.
Combine cornmeal, flour and sugar together.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, then add sour cream, cooking oil and small can cream-style corn and pour in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Get skillet out of oven.
Skillet should be hot by now.
Pour mixture into skillet and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower-pasta-chickpea soup
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart pot over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower and cook 2 minutes. Add water, broth, tomatoes, chickpeas and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Add pasta.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: steve's homemade ice cream
directions: Pour all ingredients into ice cream maker and fill with milk. Stir all ingredients until eggs are all blended well.
Plug it in or start cranking.
In about 30 minutes, you will have 1 1/2 gallons of delicious ice cream.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add berries, stirring until coated.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot with butter.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook sweet potatoes or yams; add butter.
Beat until smooth. Add eggs, sweetened condensed milk, nutmeg, salt and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: deer steak
directions: Let steaks set in milk 6 hours.
Take out; season and coat with flour.
Brown in oil.
Add onion and water.
Let it simmer 2 hours.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: just plain biscuits
directions: Stir ingredients together and knead lightly.
Spread on baking sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
Cut in diamond shapes and serve.

title: pork oriental stir-fry
directions: Marinate pork or chicken in stir-fry sauce.
In nonstick skillet, stir-fry pork (chicken) over medium to high heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Toss in large bowl with remaining ingredients.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
In skillet, heat oil to 360°.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel and fill with batter. Hold funnel over hot oil and drop batter in circular motion. Cook, turning once, until puffy and golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: any fruit cobbler pie
directions: Put the oleo in deep baking dish in a 350° oven.
Mix the sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour over the butter; do not stir.
Pour fruit in last; do not stir. Bake 1 hour.

title: swiss ham ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix in the onion, mustard, oleo, lemon juice and Swiss cheese.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles and place in a ring on a cookie sheet with the pointed ends of the rolls to the outside.
Place the broccoli mixture on the rolls.
Bring the ends of the rolls up over the mixture and tuck under.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed and freeze or chill.

title: easy main dish
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer about 5 minutes.
Also, good over spaghetti.

title: mama's homemade rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water and sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk and form soft dough (you may need more flour).
Knead until dough can be picked up without sticking to palms.
(Do this on floured surface.
It should be stiff and firm.)
Let rise for 2 hours.
Punch down and make rolls.
Let rise 2 more hours.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Slice zucchini, roll in flour or cornmeal, salt and pepper. Fry in olive oil.
Put in pot with tomatoes, cheese and oregano. Cook until cheese has melted.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham crackers and butter.
Spread on Pyrex baking dish and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature and mix with confectioners sugar.
Add Dream Whip, then cherry pie filling on top.

title: oatmeal cocoa chippers
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips, oatmeal and walnuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: annie mae's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating between each.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with milk, beating well between each addition.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut
shortening
into
flour thoroughly.
Mix in enough water until flour clears sides of bowl.
Roll out two crusts.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until mixture boils, then add peanuts and salt.
Cook to hard crack stage (285°).
Remove from stove and add baking soda, butter and vanilla.
Pour on greased pans and spread.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in square dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 7 to 10 minutes or until apples are tender.
Let stand, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Serve warm and with half and half or ice cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients (except mushrooms) to mixture and blend.
Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Fill caps and bake at 350° until lightly browned (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: swedish venison meatballs
directions: Mix meatball mixture by combining venison and ground beef with 2 eggs, 3/4 cup bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon garlic powder and 1 tablespoon onion powder.
Brown meatballs in oven or skillet and drain.

title: glazed lemon bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
In another bowl, stir together melted butter, 1 cup sugar, eggs and almond extract.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to sugar mixture.
Add lemon extract.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: ham, cheese and asparagus bake
directions: Add 1 1/2 cups hot water to stuffing mix; stir until just moistened.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Mix ham, asparagus, soup and milk in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and golden brown.

title: best flank steak
directions: Tenderize and stab with fork both sides of steak.
Mix all ingredients and add steak.
If marinade does not cover steak, add a little water.
Marinate 3 hours or overnight.
Broil 5 minutes per side for medium-rare.

title: chocolate shakes
directions: Mix together in blender and serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy strawberry ice cream
directions: Rinse and hull strawberries; slice berries in half.
In container of food processor, puree berries.
Set aside.
In a medium-size bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Set aside 10 minutes to thicken.

title: roasting ear corn bread
directions: Husk and silk the ears of corn.
Choose the freshest corn possible. Cut the corn from the cob using a very sharp knife and cutting off only top 1/4 of depth of kernels.

After cutting all around the ear, use knife to scrape out the remaining juice and pulp, scraping downward only, not back and forth. Sift cornmeal, soda, salt and sugar together. Add this mixture to the grated fresh corn; add buttermilk only as needed and stir lightly.

Add well beaten egg and lemon juice. Stir well. Add hot melted shortening and stir again until smooth. Turn into a piping hot, greased heavy 10-inch skillet, or if you prefer, corn bread stick molds and bake immediately in hot (preheated) oven at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serve at once, crusty and brown, with butter. Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: mystery cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: mini cherry cheese cakes
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Using 1 package of cupcake liners, put a vanilla wafer in each liner and fill 1/2 full with cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Put a cherry and juice on top of each cake.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel
and
cube
eggplant
and	cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and combine the remaining ingredients	in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.	Put some grated cheese on top.

title: sweet potato buns
directions: Boil and
mash	potato.
Rub in as much flour as needed to make it like bread.
Add cinnamon and sugar to yeast.
When it has risen well, work in butter.
Form small rolls on baking sheet or in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put in nonstick pan.
Keep stirring until peanut butter chips are
melted.
Put in 8-inch greased pan.
Put in refrigerator until cool; cut into squares.

title: roasted chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in hot oil in a Dutch oven 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add chicken broth and next 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, 25 minutes or until potato is tender. Add chicken, evaporated milk and noodles. Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are tender. Sprinkle with freshly ground pepper, if desired. Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 1/2 stick margarine and eggs in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, pecans and 1/2 stick margarine together.
Top casserole with these ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Mix grated cheese with butter.
Add flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough; flatten out and wrap around an olive.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm.

title: baked apples
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place baking apples in 12 x 8-inch or 9-inch baking dish.
Place 1/2 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon butter in cavity of each apple.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, until apples are tender.
Combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and water.
Spoon over baked apples.
Continue baking 10 minutes. Serve warm or cool.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken-mushroom lasagna
directions: Saute bacon; remove from skillet and saute chicken with olive oil, onion, rosemary, cloves and garlic.
Add bacon.
To skillet, add white wine, bay leaves and chicken broth.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove cloves and bay leaves and drain liquids that have not evaporated.
Add mushrooms.
Cook noodles as directed; rinse and drain.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with graham crackers.
Beat 3 cups of milk with 2 boxes of pudding and Cool Whip.
Put one layer of pudding over graham crackers, then another layer of crackers, another layer of pudding and one more layer of crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients well and spread over top layer of crackers. Chill 4 hours.

title: lazy style baked beans
directions: Place beans in a casserole.
Add sugar, catsup, bacon, mustard and liquid smoke.
Mix lightly.
Bury onion.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour.
Serves 12.

title: kay's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Grind together the flour, oatmeal, baking soda, baking powder and salt until a powder.
Gradually add this to the creamed mixture.
Then add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed french loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread in half lengthwise and slightly hollow out each half, leaving a 1/2-inch thick layer of bread.
Place bread crumbs in food processor and chop until fine crumbs.

title: pretzel salad
directions: First Layer:
Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: ham and eggs crescent pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter.
Remove from heat; stir in ham.
Place crescent dough in ungreased pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up side to form crust, sealing perforations.
Spread ham mixture over dough. Blend the remaining ingredients except chives and pour over ham. Sprinkle with chives.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes until golden brown. Serve immediately.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings or 2 dozen snacks.
If prepared ahead of time, wrap in foil and reheat at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Stir until blended and pour into greased pan.

title: sweet sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water for 7 minutes.
Drain. Melt margarine in pan.
Add sugar and flour.
Blend.
Add water, vinegar and seasonings.
Cook until thick.
Add sliced onion and cabbage.
Heat through.

title: lemon cheesecake pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine evaporated milk and pudding mix.
Beat 2 minutes.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until light.
Gradually add lemonade concentrate. Continue beating until smooth, light and fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes. Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese mixture, blending thoroughly.
Pour filling into crust.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Top with whipped cream.
Decorate as desired.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes. In casserole dish layer beef mixture and cheese.
Top with canned biscuits.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Simmer ground beef and water for 15 minutes, breaking up meat. Skim foam with spoon.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, bay leaves, chili powder, cocoa powder, garlic, vinegar, cinnamon, cumin, salt and cloves.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cover pan halfway through cooking so sauce does not get too thick.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together and pour over pineapple.
Put in greased baking dish.
Add cheese on top and sprinkle crackers over that.
Melt margarine and pour over that.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in order.
Stir lightly and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: winter fruit bowl
directions: Cut prunes and apricots into bite size pieces.
Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add prunes and apricots; remove from heat.
Cover and let soak 4 hours.
Drain. Place in a large bowl.
Cut peaches and pears into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients, except bananas.
Chill.
Add bananas just before serving.
Spoon into fruit dishes and serve. May top with a small spoonful of whipped cream.

title: cranberry holiday gelatin
directions: In a large bowl, combine the gelatin and water. Stir for 2 minutes or until dissolved. Stir in the cranberry sauce, breaking up any clumps. Stir in the pineapple. Pour into a shallow 2-quart dish. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer set on medium speed, beat the light cream cheese and fat-free
cream cheese until smooth. Beat in the sour cream and sugar. Spread over the gelatin salad and top with the walnuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Chop up corned beef. Chop up the tops of the green onions (finely).
Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate.

title: low-fat caesar salad
directions: Sprinkle daikon with salt; let stand until limp, about 15 minutes.
Squeeze daikon to remove as much water as possible.
Mix the vinegar, dashi, Mirin and sugar; add a pinch of salt. Marinate the daikon and carrot in this mixture.
Serves 4.

title: carob chip cookies with turkish apricots
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, combine butter, honey, syrup and orange juice.
With a large spoon, beat until creamy.
Mix in eggs.
Gradually add in sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in carob chips and apricots.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: molasses beans
directions: Boil lima beans on medium heat for 45 minutes.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir molasses, brown sugar, mustard and bacon into beans.
Mix well.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms and green onions in butter until slightly golden color.
Add cream and simmer for 5 minutes.
So easy, elegant and delicious!

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixing bowl mix first 3 ingredients as you would biscuits.
Pour in the dissolved yeast. Mix again.
In large bowl pour in 1 tablespoon of oil.
Put dough in bowl.
Turn over to grease all sides. Let stand until doubled in size.
Punch down and form into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sunny banana pie
directions: Slice bananas onto graham cracker crust.
Gradually add 1/2 cup milk to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pudding mix and remaining milk.
Beat slowly for 1 minute.
Pour into crust over bananas.
Garnish with coconut and chill.

title: scalloped potato casserole
directions: Make white sauce with first 4 ingredients and pepper.
Place half of potatoes in 2-quart casserole dish, cover with 1/2 of the onions and then 1/2 of the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: blueberry oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients and mix until just moist.
Fill lined or greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and sour cream in a bowl.
Blend well.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in grapes.
Cover and chill.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into ring and freeze or you can make it slushy.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Blanch 4 cups of cabbage in boiling salt water for 3 minutes. Drain.
Cover with cold water; drain.
In saucepan, saute onion and butter.
Add cabbage and toss well.
Add cream cheese and dill.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat in thoroughly.
Stir in salt, flour, soda, oats and coconut until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and bowtie pasta
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add assorted vegetables and cook until tender.
Cook pasta separately as directed.
Drain and to pasta add Parmesan cheese.
Then to chicken add Parmesan; stir.
Season with low calorie Italian dressing.
Serve.

title: beef or deer salami
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Divide in 3 equal logs 3-inches round.
Wrap in Saran Wrap; put in refrigerator for 24 hours, then unwrap.
Place on broiler pan in 325° oven for 4 hours.
Keeps 3 weeks in refrigerator or 2 months in freezer.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Melt butter and add tomato sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Simmer 18 minutes.
Add ham and 3/4 cheese until it melts.
Stir in macaroni.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti-southern style
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp and crush. Brown the onions in bacon grease. Add the ground beef, tomatoes, crumbled bacon, green peppers, kidney beans and mushrooms. Season to taste. Simmer while spaghetti cooks (about 10 minutes). Cook the spaghetti according to directions. Grease a baking dish. Place layer of spaghetti, then layer of sauce. Slice cheese over top. Bake 2 hours in slow oven (about 250°). The spaghetti can be made 1 to 2 days earlier and kept in refrigerator until baking time. It is a complete meal with a salad, drink and dessert.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; add 1 tablespoon sugar and crushed pretzels. Put in a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Melt soup, butter and cheese.
Fold sour cream into mixture. Mix the potatoes in with mixture.
Cook potatoes about 1 hour at 350°; place 1/2 stick of margarine over potaotes.
You can put corn flakes or potato chips on top.

title: mandarin orange delight
directions: Cook water, vanilla pudding, orange jello and tapioca together until they come to a boil.
Set aside until cool.
Once cooled, fold in Cool Whip and orange segments.

title: fruit 'n oat snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in airtight container up to 5 days.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in large pan.
Beat eggs and add to dry mix along with other ingredients.
Mix very well by hand.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake at 275° to 300° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and undrained cherries.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in almond extract.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges and crimp.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes, until well browned and juice bubbles through opening in crust.

title: sawyer's sunshine jello
directions: Take pineapple juice and add water to make one cup.
Add flour and sugar; cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Add egg and whisk.
Cook 1 more minute; cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and butter.
Be sure Jell-O is set up first, then add topping to Jell-O (on top only, do not mix).
After you have poured on topping, set up 2 hours.

title: deep sea delight
directions: Boil noodles 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
Add soup, asparagus or peas, tuna, green pepper and cheese.
Top with butter, bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hobo's dinner
directions: Shape hamburger meat into 1 patty.
Place patty in the center of a large piece of foil.
Put potatoes, carrots and minced onion on top of patty.
Season with salt and pepper.
Fold foil up over food.
Place into a shallow pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Yields 9 1/2 cups.
Contains per 1/2 cup serving 251 calories (11% from fat).

title: crab spread
directions: Saute almonds in butter.
Do not brown too much.
Allow cheese to soften.
Add all other ingredients and place almonds on top. Bake
in
small
dish
in
oven for 40 minutes. Serve hot with Ritz crackers.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and spices. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Spread pizza sauce on top of the cream cheese mixture. Top with green pepper and pepperoni. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes. Put cheese on top and sprinkle with Italian seasoning. Bake another 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve with corn chip scoops.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Wash chicken the night before and season with the following:
2 Tbsp. salt, 2 Tbsp. black pepper, 2 Tbsp. garlic powder and 2 Tbsp. cayenne pepper.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, put flour, black pepper, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and salt in bowl.
Cover chicken with this mixture.
Deep fry at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla, butter and nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan and dust with flour.
Cream all shortenings together.
Add sugar and salt gradually.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition. Add flavor to milk; then add alternately with flour to mixture. Put into prepared pan and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; then turn out on a rack to cool completely.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Add all ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then bake at 350° until done.

title: pineapple gratin
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, sugar and flour.
Stir in juice, sugar and flour.
Stir in pineapple and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased, shallow 2-cup baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle evenly over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in lemon rind and juice.
Beat in egg yolk, then melted butter.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg white with salt until fairly stiff peaks form, then fold into lemon mixture until no streaks of white show.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool about 15 minutes before cutting.

title: shrimp and pasta primavera
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil in medium saucepan on medium heat. Slowly, melt margarine.
Mix chicken bouillon with cup of water. Add wine, lemon and spices.
Cover and simmer on low.
Boil water for pasta.
Cut up broccoli and chop tomato into small pieces.
Add shrimp and vegetables to sauce when you boil the pasta.
They both take 3 to 5 minutes to cook.
Drain pasta and put in large pasta bowl.
Pour sauce, shrimp and vegetables over pasta and toss.
Very colorful and very good.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Melt butter in 3-quart pan. Blend in flour and stir until smooth. Slowly stir in chicken broth and pepper.
Simmer for 2 minutes. Add milk and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add crabmeat to milk mixture and salt to taste.
Remove from heat and serve. Add sherry to taste.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Spray a casserole dish with nonstick spray.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix together with rest of the ingredients.
Pour in prepared dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: andy's baked beans(the best in the world)
directions: Brown beef and 1/2 onion and remove from pan.
Fry bacon and 1/2 onion until crumbly; save 1/2 of the grease.
Microwave for 1 minute and 45 seconds the next 8 ingredients.
Add to beef and bacon the sauce mixture, the leftover grease and the beans.
Mix together.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Stir at least twice.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and salt.
Mix until smooth.
Add apples, nuts, soda and flour, then mix the topping.
Put the topping over bread before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Add carrots, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Mix together with dry ingredients. Bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: vivian's casserole
directions: Combine meat, lemon, salt, pepper, catsup, oil, onion and garlic.
Simmer slowly for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix with noodles, etc.
Bake at 325° but first sprinkle with cheese and crumbled potato chips.
Bake until it bubbles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Put layers of croutons, soup, chicken, soup, croutons and soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french cream
directions: Use your food processor and whip the cream; add powdered sugar and blend, then add the cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
This is a nice dressing for fruit salad or as a dip for fresh fruit.

title: thelma's potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Simmer ingredients (except shrimp) for about 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer another 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve on fluffy white rice.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook yams until tender.
Do not overcook.
Melt butter in a skillet.
Add sugar and juices.
Cook until syrup is formed.
Dip sweet potatoes (quartered) in syrup, then place in a Pyrex baking dish.
Dip pineapple slices in syrup and place on top of potatoes. Sprinkle with spices, if desired.
Pour rest of syrup over dish. Bake until good and hot.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Roll in sugar and bake at 350°.

title: beef and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Prepare brown rice according to directions.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large deep skillet over high heat until shimmering.
Toss beef with 2 teaspoons cornstarch in medium bowl.
Add to skillet and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Transfer to clean bowl with slotted spoon.
Add remaining teaspoon oil to skillet.
Add garlic, red pepper and onion; cook, stirring, 30 seconds.
Stir in broccoli and sauce.
Dissolve remaining teaspoon cornstarch in chicken broth.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring, until broccoli is tender, 5 minutes.
Return beef to skillet with watercress and cook, stirring, 1 minute more.
Serve with brown rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato delight
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix together with other ingredients (except potato chips).
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Top with crushed potato chips.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Slice potatoes and arrange in a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Layer with minced onion and top with shredded cheese.
Pour milk over mixture and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar. Wash broccoli; cut into pieces. Cut scallions into pieces. Cook bacon; cut into pieces. Mix together. Put cheese and mixture of mayo over top. Mix well.

title: iced coffee
directions: Make coffee in pot (very strong).
Then add sugar and vanilla; mix well and chill.
When serving, whip cream.
Add ice cubes in a large wine glass; pour in coffee to 2/3 full.
Spoon whipping cream on top of coffee.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryer; salt and let stand for a while.
When ready to cook, rinse excess salt off.
Drop in a paper bag with flour and shake well.
Have a frying pan hot with Crisco (at least 1/3 full). Drop chicken into hot grease.
Cover; turn heat down to low.
Let steam about 10 minutes.
Turn heat up; let brown before turning. Turn and let brown on other side.
Take up and place on paper towels to take up excess grease.

title: lo-cal pseudo bloody mary sipper
directions: Combine.
Chill.
Serve in glass with stalk of celery placed in each glass.
Makes 8 servings, 28 calories per serving.

title: polynesian ham loaf
directions: Put meat in baking pan.
Cut into strips, but don't cut through the bottom.
Put mustard between slices.
Cut pineapple in half and arrange between slices.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake according to manufacturer's directions.

title: rhubarb blueberry jam
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar and let set overnight.
In the morning, boil rhubarb and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add blueberry pie filling and boil 5 minutes more.
Add raspberry jello and stir until dissolved.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: skillet apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and sugar into iron skillet.
Combine salad oil and egg.
Add nuts and apples.
Stir all together with dry ingredients and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil for 12 minutes. Ladle into hot jars and seal tightly.

title: crabmeat beer puffs
directions: Puffs:
In saucepan, melt 1 stick butter; add beer.
Bring to boil.
Add flour.
Mix; add salt and 1 egg at a time.
Mix thoroughly until mixture comes away from pan.
Remove from heat. Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: artichoke tossed salad
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, vinegar, sugar, garlic, dry mustard, salt, pepper and onions into a large jar.
Cover and shake until well mixed.
Add artichokes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Brown croutons in butter, stirring until toasted on all sides.
Toss greens and radishes in a large serving bowl.
Add artichokes and dressing.
Toss well. Add avocados and croutons.
Serves 12. Croutons are best served warm. Reheat just before serving, if needed.

title: kookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all items except 1/4 cup nuts. Mix well.
Press into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Chop egg and slice olives.
Rinse shrimp in cold water.
Place in mixing bowl and break up finely with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients, except olives; mix well.
Chill.
Garnish with olives and additional picante sauce, if desired.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: Cream butter, then add powdered sugar, cornstarch, flour and lemon rind; mix well.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.
Shape dough into balls and drop into chopped nuts.
Flatten with bottom of a drinking glass that has been dipped in flour.
Put nut side up on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes; cool. To prepare frosting, combine the powdered sugar, melted butter and lemon juice.
Frost cookies when completely cool.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Add egg.
Sift flour in gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet, about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, eggs and oil until crumbly*.
Press lightly in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients well. Pour over mushrooms.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: breakfast(sausage)
directions: Brown sausage.	Tear bread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Mix eggs and milk.
Beat and pour over bread and sausage.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chopstick chicken
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup chow mein noodles, chicken, celery, cashews, onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated.
Garnish with drained, canned mandarin oranges.

title: peanut butter fruit dip
directions: Mix milk and 5 tablespoons of water.
Slowly mix up peanut butter stirring in honey.
Add remaining water a little at a time until proper consistency.
Mix until very smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve with fruit.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°, using greased and floured tube pan.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese to top and bake 5 minutes longer or until set.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate.
Mix until coated. Spread on waxed paper; let cool.
Break into small pieces.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook chicken in covered saucepan with carrot, onion, celery and salt in enough water to cover all.
Simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.
Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package.
Place broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Arrange cooled, deboned chicken on top of broccoli.
Top with cream of mushroom soup and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese on top.
Heat in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Combine berries and sugar; mash and let sit 15 minutes. Combine water and Sure-Jell in separate pan; boil 1 minute.
Pour water and Sure-Jell over berries and sugar mixture and stir 3 minutes. Pour in jar.
Let set for 24 hours.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer a few hours before serving.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order listed:
lettuce, celery, onions, radishes, green pepper and green peas, in 4-quart mixing bowl.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except almonds and blend.
Spoon into 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Heat in oven or microwave until warm (oven, 350°). Dip your favorite crackers into the hot spread.

title: eggless homemade ice cream
directions: In an ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients. Freeze per ice cream maker instructions.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add vinegar, vanilla and melted oleo.
Blend in sugar
and
meal.
Pour
into
prepared pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Leave Philadelphia cream cheese out for 2 or 3 hours to soften.
Then put in a bowl, add shredded ham, Italian dressing and onions.
Mix well.
Form into a ball and chill.
Roll in pecans; serve with crackers.
Sprinkle parsley over the top or set the cheese ball on lettuce leaves.
For a party, it is a quick, filling snack, or use for an appetizer.
Can make it with many variations.
You can use any kind of meat and crackers or you may garnish it.

title: chicken breasts with rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover bottom with raw rice.
Mix soups, milk, butter and wine.
Pour about 1/3 of mixture over rice.
Place chicken on rice (do not overlap).
Pour remainder of soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and almonds on top. Bake at 275°, uncovered, for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't disturb until ready to serve.

title: german hot slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and place in cooking pot. Add water, pepper, salt, sugar and butter. Cover and cook on medium heat until soft, about 30 minutes.
If water cooks up too fast, add a little more.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Be sure and work enough flour in until your dough handles good and is not sticky.
Put in large oiled bowl and oil top of dough.
Let rise about 2 hours or until double in size.
Then work some dough and pinch off rolls.
Turn in oil and let rise on oiled pan, about 2 hours.
Makes about 40 rolls. Bake at 450°.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Combine apples, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Combine lemon juice and water and pour over apples.
Mix butter, sugar and flour until like cornmeal and pat on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or cream.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine undrained corn, muffin mix, margarine (divided), sour cream, eggs and cheese.
Reserve 1/3 of the cheese for topping. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add remaining cheese and bake until cheese is melted.

title: no crust spinach pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in an oiled pie plate or spring-form pan. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to boil in a saucepan and add at once to flour mixture while still hot.
Cream well and pour on greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice while still hot.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use 1 tablespoon per cup of boiling water.

title: banana protein shake
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Pour into frosty glasses and garnish with sprinkle of ground cinnamon, if desired.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling and simmer 3 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: caramel corn
directions: Microwave butter, sugar and corn syrup on High for 9 to 12 minutes.
Mix popcorn and peanuts together.
Cover with hot liquid.
Press immediately.

title: crabbies
directions: Let margarine and cheese spread soften together at room temperature.
Mix with mayonnaise, garlic powder and seasoned salt.
Add crab meat.
Mix and spread on split muffins.
Freeze 10 minutes if for immediate use.
Cut into quarters and broil until bubbly.

title: clams casino
directions: Steam the clams and drain.
(Save the juice.)
Mix cheese, pepper, garlic and sherry. Spoon over the clams.
Add some of the reserved juice.
Melt butter.
Mix in bread crumbs and spoon over cheese mixture. Spoon more juice on top.
Top each clam shell with small piece of bacon.
Broil until bacon is done.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in bottle or jar and serve over fruit salad.

title: harold's monday night clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Saute next 5 ingredients in renderings.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low for at least 2 hours.
Steak sauce or milk may be added before serving.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Blend with mixer the first three ingredients.
This will be doughy.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the last four ingredients together very well.
Pour this over the first three ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked rice broccoli(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and celery in butter. Mix in a big bowl, cooked rice, onion, celery, broccoli, mushroom soup, water chestnuts and cheese.
Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red peanut patty
directions: Cook to soft ball.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter and red food coloring.
Stir until consistency of fudge. Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve
the
yeast
in
the
warm water.
Mix the hot water and milk together.	Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Add the yeast that has been dissolved in the warm water.
Mix the shortening mixture
by slowly adding a little flour at a time, until it is stiff enough to handle.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until creamy.
Add oil and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder together.
Add dry ingredients to egg and sugar mixture.
Add zucchini (don't peel) and walnuts.
Mix and bake in 2 to 3 loaf pans (depends on thickness you prefer).
Fill pans about 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake in greased and floured pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: swiss chicken
