directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place Swiss cheese on top of chicken.
Spoon soup over Swiss cheese.
Top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches with juices in pie pan.
Add nutmeg and vanilla. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over peaches.
Dribble melted butter over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla.
Add eggs, beating well.
Mix in flour.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours or until cake tests done.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Grease cookie sheet and bake cake 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix instant pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Spread over the cake. Drain pineapple and spread over top.
Spread Cool Whip over that and then spread the coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: corn fritters
directions: Put 1-inch vegetable oil in skillet.
Blend egg and milk.
Add pancake mix, stirring just until smooth.
Fold in corn.
To ensure lightness, do not beat.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil at 325°. Cook slowly until golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Serve as a vegetable or with syrup, if desired.
Makes approximately 24 fritters.

title: armenian pilaf(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in pot and brown the vermicelli noodles (saute them).
Add rice.
Add chicken broth.
Cover and cook on low flame until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Let rest for 15 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Chop or grate potatoes and onions.
Place all ingredients in large casserole.
Bake in slow oven (250° to 300°), covered. Uncover last hour.
Takes about 5 hours.
Very tasty and a family favorite.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and saute onion, celery, parsley and mushrooms.
Pour over bread cubes in a large mixing bowl.
Add all seasonings and toss together.
Pour in enough broth to moisten. Add eggs and mix well.
Pour in slow cooker set on high for 45 minutes.
Then reduce to low and cook for 4 to 6 hours.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Blend sugar and cocoa in 2-quart bowl.
Add milk and butter. Cook in microwave oven 2 minutes.
(Note:
Do not mix these ingredients.)
Remove from oven; stir just until mixed.
Add vanilla, stir and add peanut butter.
Pour into greased container. Place in refrigerator 1 hour.
Cut to serve.

title: butterscotch goodies
directions: In double boiler, melt chips and peanut butter.
Then add vanilla.
Take off heat and add marshmallows.
Pour into a greased pan.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cream together beaten egg, sugar and shortening.
Add vanilla and pumpkin last.
Then add dates or raisins and nuts.
Beat until all blended.
(May add up to 1/4 cup extra flour if batter is too moist.)
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° until light brown, about 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Blend lemonade, powdered sugar and berries. Add Cool Whip. Blend again. Add ice and keep blending. Add rum and blend again.

title: boeuf bourguignon(beef burgundy)
directions: Toss the meat in flour, salt and pepper and brown in butter and oil.
Add consomme, wine, onion, carrots, garlic, bay leaf and thyme.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is tender.
Add parsley, small whole onions and mushrooms just before serving and simmer until hot.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix bread crumbs, milk and ground beef into balls. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs. Cook 45 to 60 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: 3 meat cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
Make two molds.
Place in greased pan.
Cut cheese into 1 inch x 1/8-inch wide sticks.
Press cheese sticks into molds all the way down, covering top over. Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven or until brown.
Open 1 can tomato sauce.
Pour over top.
Let set 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: amish dish
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal rocks(carmie woods)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and add beaten eggs and vanilla. Mix the rest of the dry ingredients.
Sprinkle over the raisins, or nuts, and combine the mixtures.
Add only enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Drop on a greased pan, one inch apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fried zucchini
directions: After washing, slice zucchini and season to taste.
Mix the milk, eggs and 1/4 teaspoon seasoning salt.
Roll in flour and fry in hot oil until brown.
For a heavier batter, use evaporated milk.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add them first before butter. Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hot waffle iron.
Cook until light brown.

title: plum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well in the mixer.
Pour into tube cake pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test 10 minutes before the hour, as may be done a little early.

title: green molded salad
directions: Stir all together and chill until firm.

title: luscious chocolate cake
directions: Grease oblong pan (do not flour).
Layer pecans and coconut.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix in chili beans and add cheese.
Melt it all together in a skillet.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes.
Combine all in large bowl and sprinkle with corn chips.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place 1 stick ham and 1 slice of cheese on each fillet.
Roll up.
Secure with toothpicks and dredge in flour.
Arrange in greased baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: wheat germ oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to shortening mixture.
Stir in wheat germ, nuts and oats.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: martini chicken
directions: Season chicken pieces with
salt
and pepper.
Place in baking dish.
Combine
remaining
ingredients.
Marinate
1/2 hour or longer, turning once
or
twice.
Cook
on grill, skin side down. Grill 10 minutes, basting with marinade.
Grill 25 to 30 minutes or until
chicken
pieces are tender and well browned.

title: okurkovi salat po cesku(cucumber salad, czech style)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Drop in slightly salted water for 30 minutes; drain well.
Add sugar and mild vinegar to taste. Stir.
Add sour cream; stir well and enjoy (salad dressing may be used).
Chopped onion may be added, if desired.
Delicious with any menu.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells and drain.
Prepare spinach as directed.
Open hot spinach into a bowl and mix with Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses. Stir until cheese melts.
Fill each shell with a spoonful of spinach/cheese mix and place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce with or without browned meat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sis. deluish's half pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar slowly and cream well.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat.
Add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add milk; beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Cover and chill overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables of your choice.

title: kathleen's chili
directions: Saute bacon, garlic and beef.
Combine in pot the onions, celery, green pepper, mustard, chili powder, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, tomato sauce or paste and whole tomatoes.
Add meat mixture.
Cook and simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Add the 2 cups of red kidney beans at the last hour.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine and press in bottom of a 9-inch pie shell. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt
and
water
in a glass bowl; let stand at room
temperature
hours.
Add sugar and vinegar, stirring until sugar
is dissolved.
Pack into 1 pint freezer containers, leaving 1-inch
space
at
top.
Cover and freeze overnight or up to 6 weeks.

title: cottage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in order listed.
Do not stir.
Let stand overnight.
Cover with foil.
Put ingredients in a large bowl or pan.

title: fat-free macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni (omit salt and oil).
Drain, return to pan over very low heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 3.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onions, celery, peppers and garlic in oil until soft. Add tomatoes, stock, tomato soup, Ro-tel tomatoes, water and spices.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours on low heat.
Ten minutes before serving, add tortilla squares.
In individual soup bowls, place any of the following:
chopped chicken, avocados, grated cheese, green onions and sour cream.
Pour in soup on top.

title: fruit dish
directions: Shake pineapple juice with the lemon instant pudding and pour over fruit; mix.
Can make the night before.
Before serving, add the banana.
Serves 8.

title: country cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well until blended.
Add flour; sprinkle soda and salt over flour.
Beat until no trace of flour can be seen.
With wooden spoon, work in oats and coconut.
Bake at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together well (preferably in a blender.)
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pie filling and crushed pineapple with the juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.
Combine remaining ingredients for topping.
Spread cream cheese mixture over chilled Jell-O.
Cut into squares.

title: punch
directions: Chill.
Add ice cubes or frozen turks head of juice.

title: skillet corn
directions: Cook and stir all ingredients in skillet over medium heat until margarine is melted. Cook and cover over low heat until corn is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown the beef in the fat.
Add the sliced onions and minced garlic; brown.
Mix together the catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Stir in the vinegar, brown sugar, paprika, salt, dry mustard and red pepper.
Add the 2 cups water.
Cover and simmer for 2 to 2 1/4 hours.
Add more water, if necessary.
Thicken with the 2 tablespoons flour and 1/4 cup water.
Pour Goulash over cooked noodles.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot oil.
Add onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to meat.
Cover and simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper; cook another 30 minutes (or longer).
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into meat mixture.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes longer.
Remove garlic.
Serve over hot rice.

title: peppermint supreme
directions: Place wafers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate in margarine. Add sugar, egg yolks, pecans and vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread chocolate mixture over wafer crumbs.
Spread softened ice cream on top.
Freeze.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: pennsylvania dutch potatoes
directions: Boil together potatoes, celery and onion (if using instant potatoes, boil celery and onion).
Mash using a real masher; add bread crumbs, eggs and margarine. If dry, add a little milk.
Can be served as is, or refrigerated in casserole and heated in 325° oven for 1 hour.
I have added 1/2 chopped cabbage and called in Colcannon.

title: chicken quesadilla
directions: Place a tortilla in a lightly buttered skillet.
Layer with 1/2 of cheese, 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of salsa or picante.
Place another tortilla on top.
Repeat layering.
Top with last tortilla. Drizzle margarine on top.
Slowly cook to heat through and crisp the tortilla.
Do not burn.
Carefully turn and finish cooking. Can be placed in a 325° oven to keep warm.
Cut into 8 wedges and serve.

title: tex mex(serves 16 generously)
directions: Mash avocados with a fork and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Chop tomatoes, green onions and black olives.
Mix mayo and sour cream together with taco mix (envelope).
You are ready to assemble.
Spread refried beans into bottom of shallow dish. Add avocado mixture.
Next, add sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle tomatoes, black olives and onion next.
Finish off with shredded Jack and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Fritos or rounded nacho chips.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 pans at 350°.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix together Crisco oil or oleo and sugar.
Cream thoroughly. Add eggs.
Beat well and add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, ground cloves and nutmeg.
Fold into the batter apples, raisins and nuts.
Spoon into tube pan or make hole in square pan at 325°.

title: applesauce cupcakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Put in paper cups in cake pan and fill about half full.
Bake in 300° oven about 30 minutes.

title: flossie's pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Break eggs into another bowl.
Add pumpkin and butter.
Whisk until well blended, stir in chocolate chips.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Fold in until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put in muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cecilia's pretzel salad
directions: Mix oleo and sugar together; add pretzels and put all in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Smooth with back of spoon to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix Dream Whip following instructions on package.
Mix the Dream Whip and cream cheese until fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of mixture over the pretzel crust.
Add crushed pineapple.
Pour remaining cream cheese mixture over top. Top with reserved crushed pretzels and/or cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crumble
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch square pan or a 10 x 6-inch rectangular baking dish.
Arrange apples in dish.
Mix Bisquick, sugar and egg until crumbly; sprinkle over apples. Drizzle margarine over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon and allspice over top.
Bake until topping is golden brown and apples are tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "mexican breakfast"
directions: Scramble eggs along with the rest of ingredients.
Roll scrambled eggs in flour tortilla and top with lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: almond-cranberry squash bake
directions: In large bowl, combine the squash, 2 tablespoons butter, salt, cinnamon and allspice and mix well.
Transfer to 2-quart baking dish.
Stir cranberry sauce until softened and spoon over squash.
Combine almonds, brown sugar and remaining 2 tablespoons butter and mix well.
Sprinkle almond mixture over cranberry sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar and set aside. Mix in a saucepan the butter, Crisco, cocoa and Coke, bringing to a rapid boil.
Pour over dry mixture (flour and sugar). Add buttermilk and soda together and add to mixture along with eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix together and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low-fat creamy carrot soup
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add carrots and cook for 5 minutes.
Add broth. Bring to a boil.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Puree in electric blender or food mill.
Pour into saucepan; add milk, salt, nutmeg and pepper. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes; do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: lefse
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Knead well.
Using 1/2 cup at a time, roll paper thin on floured board.
Bake on lightly greased griddle, turning often to avoid scorching.
Should be slightly golden, but never crisp.
Wipe griddle clean each time.

title: broken glass dessert
directions: Set red and green gelatin in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans the night before preparing dessert.
Cube both pans of gelatin. Prepare lemon gelatin, replacing hot water with pineapple juice. Use quick set method by replacing cold water with ice cubes.
Fold whipped topping in the lemon gleatin.
Mix the red and green cubes alternately in one of the pans.
Cover with lemon mixture.
Add more red and green cubes, layering alternately until lemon mixture is used.
Put in refrigerator until set; then serve.

title: divinity candy
directions: Before you start cooking your syrup, beat your egg whites to a peak, very stiff, also have large area buttered to spoon drop your candy onto.
Add sugar, water and syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil and cook to hard ball stage in cold water.
Add syrup to beaten egg whites, a little at a time.
Add vanilla; add pecans. Beat until stiff enough to hold its form when it is dropped.
If it gets too stiff, can soften with a little hot water.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips and oleo in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat for 8 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Blend peppers and vinegar in blender, one cup at a time.
Put sugar in large pot.
Add vinegar and pepper.
Boil 2 or 3 minutes. Add Certo and coloring.
Stir 3 minutes after it comes to a boil. Skim off foam.
Pour in jars.
Cover with wax.
You can make it red by using sweet red peppers and red coloring.
Makes 6 jars or 2 small jars.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; take out to cool.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Debone chicken.
Mix ingredients together and top with grated cheese or Velveeta.

title: mexican nachos
directions: Spray pie plate with nonstick cooking oil spray.
Spread beans on pie plate.
Sprinkle on cumin and garlic powder, then sprinkle on picante sauce, green onions and finally with cheese.
Place under broiler to melt cheese.

title: cottage fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut potatoes into 8 wedges each and arrange in a single layer on prepared baking sheet.
Sprinkle with generous amount of paprika.
Bake in preheated oven 12 minutes.
Turn potatoes over; sprinkle with more paprika.
Bake 12 minutes or until lightly browned and fork-tender.

title: fajitas perry style
directions: 1st Step:
Marinate steak in dry and liquid fajita seasoning for at least 1 hour.
Then place in hot skillet with Italian dressing.
Brown and remove.
Place on paper towels to drain.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Gradually add sugar.
Drain cherries and save juice.
Cut cherries and add to mixture.
Sift flour together with baking powder and salt.
Add all dry ingredients with nuts, alternating with the cherry juice so that some of juice is added last.
Bake 1 hour in greased loaf pan at 350°.
Test the loaf after 1 hour, as it may take about 10 minutes more.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash until tender in salted water.
Mash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers for four
directions: Parboil the green peppers; drain and set aside to cool.
In a thick pan, melt butter and saute onions.
When onion is well sauteed, mix in the chopped sausage.
Stir mixture until sausage is well browned.
Mix in the rice and stir together until the rice is browned.
Mix in a few cups at a time of warm water mixture to the rice.
As the rice absorbs the water, continue to replace with more water and stir frequently.
Continue this procedure until rice is fully cooked, then salt and pepper to taste.
Remove rice from heat and mix in desired amount of Parmesan cheese.
Mix well, then fill each pepper with the rice mixture.
Place one slice of Mozzarella cheese on top with a dot of butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until the cheese has melted thoroughly.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel and quarter the apples.
Roll the biscuits, one at a time, and cut in half. Roll biscuits around quarter of apple. Place in sheet cake pan.
This will make 20 dumplings.
Mix the sugar, water and vanilla.
Let melt on warm burner and pour over apples.
Melt the margarine and pour over the apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good served hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: english apple pie
directions: Bake at 350° in square pyrex pan. Serve hot or cold with ice cream, whipped cream, milk, or cream.

title: ham salad
directions: Boil your noodles in pot until firm but done.
While cooking, dice ham and cheese into small pieces on cutting board.
Leave peas frozen until pasta is ready to be drained.
Put peas into colander then pour pasta and hot water onto them to drain.
Put peas and pasta into bowl.
Mix in ham and cheese; season with Italian dressing.
Great if you have no time to make a fancy meal. Approximate cost:

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Add the crumbled bacon and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Blend well, then toss lightly with the broccoli-bacon mix.
Make sure all surfaces are covered.
Add cheese and toss again.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch lace cookies
directions: Add sugar to butter; pour over rolled oats.
Let stand at room temperature overnight so oats absorb butter.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
in	skillet;
add onion and cook 3 minutes. Add broccoli, rice and soup.
Pour into casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: dad dicke's brook trout
directions: Be sure the heads and tails are left on the fish.
The fish may be 10 to 12-inches long.
Wash and dry.
Beat egg; add a little water and mix.
Season cracker crumbs.
Roll fish in egg mixture and then in seasoned cracker crumbs.
Put shortening in frypan (not too much, these are not French fried).
Cook over not too high a heat.
When brown on one side, turn very carefully with a spatula to cook the other side.
When done on that side, cook for a little bit on their backs and stomachs.
Just before they are done, add a little butter to get that good flavor.

title: billie's veggie pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto pizza pan; brush with beaten egg and bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and remove ends of cucumbers; slice with skins on.
Peel and slice onions.
Layer cucumbers, onions and salt; let stand 3 hours in refrigerator.
Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil; add well rinsed and drained cucumbers and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes approximately 12 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in prepared pie crust.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until well beaten.
Add sugar and mix.
Add cream, mixing continuously.
Mix until all sugar is suspended and mixture is creamy.
Add vanilla and salt and mix.
Pour batter into 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Add half and half to fill line (no more than one pint).
Freeze.

title: italian breaded pork chops
directions: In bowl, mix parsley, garlic salt, pepper and olive oil; mix well.
In another bowl, add cracker meal.
Dip chops in cracker meal, then in oil mixture and back in cracker meal.
(Add any leftover parsley mixture to top of each chop.) Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on thickness of chops.

title: turnip green soup
directions: Cover beans with water.
Add ham and cook about 2 hours.
Add onion, potato and turnip greens.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Add sausage.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook another 15 minutes. Freezes well.

title: buffalo stew
directions: Brown meat and onions, add all other ingredients as they come out of can. Heat until thoroughly warm, 10 to 20 minutes.

title: southwestern sausage and cheese casserole
directions: The day before serving, prepare casserole.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish and layer half of chilies, half of tortilla strips, half of sausage and half of cheese.
Repeat with remaining chilies, tortilla strips, sausage and cheese.

title: easy lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan
mix
first
ingredients.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Cook	and
stir
over
high
heat until mixture begins to
boil.
Reduce heat, cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Mix small
amount
of
hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to hot
mixture.
Bring
to boiling point and cook another 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter and slowly add lemon juice.
Pour
into	pastry	shell.	Spread	meringue over filling, sealing edges to pastry.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Cook sugar, soda and milk to fairly hard boil.
Add butter before removing from heat.
Beat until it begins to cream.
Add nuts and pour into buttered Pyrex dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pink salad freeze
directions: Combine honey and cream cheese until well blended.
Stir in fruit.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 5-cup molds or 6 (3/4-cup) molds and freeze until firm.
Unmold and serve.

title: mexican chicken wings
directions: Place all ingredients, except chicken wings, in a large glass bowl and mix well.
Add the chicken and turn to coat with the margarine.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain wings.
Arrange on large baking tray.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender and the juices run clear when pierced at the thickest part.
Heat scale: medium to hot.

title: old fashioned potato salad
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator until served.

title: apple pudding from a friend
directions: Cream butter and sugar very thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together and stir into creamed mixture.
Blend in the apples and nuts.
Pour all into a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done by testing.

title: easy baked corn casserole
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg and sour cream.
Stir in corn bread mix, salt and pepper.
Add corn; mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate-peanut butter cookie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Remove cookie dough from wrapper. With floured fingers, press dough in bottom of ungreased spring-form pan. Bake for 14 to 18
minutes until golden brown. Cool 15 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all together, beat 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple (juice and all).
Add nuts and marshmallows; fold in Cool Whip.
Let set in refrigerator for a few hours before serving.

title: cherry eggnog quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3 (5 1/2 x 3-inch) mini loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and nutmeg in large bowl.
Stir eggnog, melted butter, eggs and vanilla in medium bowl until well blended.
Add eggnog mixture to flour mixture.
Mix just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in pecans and cherries.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and cool on wire rack.

title: big red punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
During freezing process, stir several times (to make sure mixture is mixed).
When ready to serve, break up frozen juice to make a slush-like drink.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine
salt,
cinnamon,
vanilla, molasses, sugar and egg. Then
add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully!

title: topping for apple, blueberry or cherry pie
directions: Mix all together and use as needed.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Make a syrup with 1 cup sugar and water by heating to a boil. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add beaten egg and beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Turn batter into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Put berries over batter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Pour syrup over fruit and batter.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven 45 minutes.
There will be a cake layer on top with fruit at the bottom.
We usually double the recipe.
Also good with fresh peaches or canned cherries.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into balls. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes (check after 15 minutes). Makes 60.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup margarine until smooth.
Add flour and blend well.
Chill for about 2 hours, or overnight. Shape dough into 24 one-inch balls, press into 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Blend egg, brown sugar, vanilla, 1 tablespoon margarine, salt and pecans in small bowl.
Fill pastry cups with egg mixture. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: rhubarb meringue pie
directions: Place diced rhubarb in colander.
Pour boiling water over rhubarb and drain.
Beat egg yolks with sugar, flour and salt. Add rhubarb.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Beat egg whites with 3 tablespoons sugar until meringue forms stiff peaks.
Spread over warm pie and return to oven until meringue is brown (approximately 10 minutes).

title: it's a frenchee
directions: Prepare three cheese sandwiches using salad dressing as desired.
Cut off crusts and diagonally slice sandwiches into quarters.
Beat together egg, milk, flour and salt.
Dip sandwich triangles in egg batter and roll in finely crushed corn flakes. Can be frozen, if desired, until needed.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Brown meat.
Add seasoning and about 1 cup of water.
Cook for 3 or 4 minutes.
Spoon into pie dish lined with tortillas. Sprinkle chilies on top.
Then cheese.
Pour eggs and milk that have been mixed together over all.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: taco salsa dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain well.
Add taco seasoning and salsa dip.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in Velveeta; let melt. Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
To keep warm, put in crock-pot.
May be frozen or kept in refrigerator.

title: burnet dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, chopped burnet, chopped chives, chopped lettuce and salt and pepper with dry white wine and leave overnight if real cucumber flavor is desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: deviled eggs - for lunch
directions: Start oven at moderately hot (400°).
Place stuffed eggs in lightly greased casserole.
Drain juice from mushrooms, saving 1/4 cup juice.
Blend juice with mayonnaise and milk in saucepan over low heat and stir until smooth.
Add mushrooms and mix.
Pour over eggs in casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes or until crumbs are browning.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain off drippings.
Remove from heat.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; pour water over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: craft . . . lace easter egg
directions: Spread the newspaper to protect your work surface.
Now blow up the balloons.
Pour glue into the pie pan and immerse long pieces of string in the glue.
Carefully take the string out of the glue, letting the excess drip off.
Spread the glued string on the balloon, making a lacy pattern.
Repeat until the balloon is covered in an attractive design.
Let the glue dry, then pop the balloon.

title: candied dill strips
directions: Boil 35 minutes in mixture and can.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Frost, if desired with cream cheese frosting.

title: hot sauce
directions: Boil 30 minutes or until. Can in hot jars. Turn upside-down to cool.

title: apple cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each apple into eight pieces. Unroll crescent rolls; separate into eight triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangle strips.

title: not edible cornmeal dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Add more water to form smooth dough.
Model as any dough.

title: company beets
directions: Cook brown sugar, cornstarch and salt with pineapple (and juice) until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter, lemon juice and beets.
Heat through.

title: soccer squares
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in a pot over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir often.
Then remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and cereal; mix well.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hearty beef and vegetable soup
directions: Place beef, soup bone, salt and 4 quarts of water in a very large kettle.
Cover; bring to boiling.
Skim surface.
Add cabbage, onion, carrot, celery, green pepper and tomatoes.
Bring to boiling; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, for 3 1/2 hours.
Remove meat and bone; discard bone.
Let meat cool.
Cut into cubes; add to soup. Refrigerate several hours.
Just before serving soup, skim fat from surface.
Slowly heat soup to boiling.
Store leftover soup, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 6 1/2 quarts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
It makes its own crust.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Boil together sugar, cornstarch and water until clear and starts to thicken.
Take off stove and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Pour 1/2 mixture in baked pie shell; layer grapefruit sections that have the thin lining removed.
Add the rest of glaze and add another layer of grapefruit.
Cool rest of the way in refrigerator; cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Blend Italian dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Layer ingredients in tall clear serving bowl.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients together.
Crumble over potato mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain well.
Cook noodles until tender.
In a 9 x 12-inch pan layer hamburger, noodles, vegetable soup, water and salt.
Mix tomato juice with dash of Tabasco sauce. Pour over top.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add meat and seasonings and brown. Add beans and soup.
Pour in greased casserole and spoon mashed potatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
A good dish to prepare ahead of time.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup in heavy pan.
Boil to medium stage (240°).
Slowly pour half over beaten egg whites, beating constantly. Cook remaining syrup to very hard ball stage (265°). Beat syrup into candy mix. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: frozen cucumber pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover in a container and refrigerate 24 hours.
Fill freezer containers and freeze.

title: homemade paste(for the kids on a rainy day)
directions: Mix the salt, sugar, alum and flour together.
Stir in a small amount of water to a consistency to pour.
Add 2 cups of hot water and boil until clear.
Seal in small jars for long-keeping periods of time.
A few drops of oil of cloves give a good smell to it.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into large casserole dish.

title: chinese noodle casserole
directions: Mix all above ingredients together; pour into greased casserole and bake in 375° oven about 30 minutes or until nicely browned on top.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding (best with evaporated milk), then chill.
Arrange in layers the vanilla wafers, bananas (sliced) and pudding. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush vanilla wafers on top.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butter and sugar together in cast-iron skillet.
Cook until it turns a honey brown color.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
While still hot, place 6 Hershey bars on top.
When melted, spread over top of toffee.
Sprinkle with nuts.
After completely cooled, break into pieces.

title: pickled tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes and put some in a 3 litre jar.
Put in three different relishes: aromatic herbs, pepper and garlic.
Fill with boiling pickle solution.

title: lo-cal pineapple cheese salad ring
directions: Drain syrup from pineapple.
Measure and add enough water to make 2 1/2 cups.
Heat to boiling; remove from heat.
Add lemon and lime gelatins and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites, then fold in drained pineapple, cheese and almonds.
Pour into 2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Turn out onto large plate and tuck lettuce frills under edges.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Also good with cheese added on top about 10 minutes before it is finished cooking.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry and plain gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill to firm.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place hash browns in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix with cheese, sour cream and onion.
Cut butter into small chunks and dot evenly over all.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: serviceman's delight cookies
directions: Blend butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 cup flour.
Press in an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut coffeecake(in honor of lottie direct)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large electric-mixer bowl, combine cake mix, soup, water, eggs and lemon rind.
Beat until blended, following package directions.
Stir in 1 cup of the coconut, the pineapple and the walnuts.
Spread batter evenly in pan.

title: heart smart honey poppy seed dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients together in small bowl.
Great over fresh fruit salads.

title: cousin jean's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar, and eggs.
Gradually add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, and salt.
Roll into 1-1/2 inch balls.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Roll balls in mixture.
Bake at 350 for 8-10 minutes.

title: mexican rose
directions: Simmer in crock-pot until bubbly.
Serve over corn chips.

title: company baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large crock-pot and cook on low for 3 hours.
Continue cooking until ready to eat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring everything (but baking soda) to a boil.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir until creamy.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread in greased pans.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: crab rounds
directions: Remove any remaining pieces of shell or cartilage from crabmeat.
In bowl, combine crab, cream cheese, parsley and onion. Mix well.
Spread each slice of bread with heaping tablespoonful of crab mixture and roll bread in jelly roll fashion.
Cut roll into thirds.
Cut bacon slices in half.
Roll one piece of bacon around each bread roll.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, turning once during baking.

title: grandmama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all of this with a wire whisk.
Cook in microwave (stirring every few minutes) or on top of double boiler until pudding is thickened.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: zucchini gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray bottom and sides of round, ovenproof baking dish (approximately 9-inch wide and 1-inch deep; a pie dish may be used).

title: seven layer fiesta dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a shallow serving dish.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning; spread over beans.
Top with cheese, tomato onion, dollop of guacamole and olives.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in cans of fruit.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Sprinkle walnuts next.
Place pats of margarine evenly over cake mix.
Last, sprinkle 1/4 cup brownulated sugar over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with dollop of whipped topping or ice cream.

title: south sea salad
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain. Combine rotini, tuna, oranges, celery and apple in large bowl.
In small bowl, blend cottage cheese, mayo, seasoned salt and lemon juice.
Add to rotini mixture.
Toss to coat.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Stir gently before serving and top with paprika.

title: baked pork chops and apples
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add pork chops, 3 at a time, and brown.
Remove chops from skillet.
Add onion, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, until onion is tender.
Stir in water.
Arrange pork chops and apple slices in shallow baking dish.
Add onion mixture.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, until pork chops are tender.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mixture will be stiff.
Add 1 cup well drained pineapple and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for about 12 to 15 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, frost with icing.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, flour, water, vinegar.
Cook until thick; add salt, butter and beets.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook chicken about 1 1/2 hours in boiling water.
When slightly cool, pick the meat off.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with the broth from the chicken.
Add chicken pieces.
Heat on stove until hot. Serve over rice or cooked biscuits.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken.
Bake skin side up for 1 hour at 350°.
Turn over and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: baked chicken wingettes
directions: Mix jam and onion soup mix.
Place wingettes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour mixture over wings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in well-greased baking dish.
Mix rice and soups together and pour over chicken.
Do not cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt margarine in fondue pot.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk gradually while stirring over medium heat.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and cheese.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
When cheese is melted, add Worcestershire sauce and onion flakes.
Mix well.
Dip large bread cubes, ham cubes, fresh broccoli, cauliflower or whatever you'd like that is dipable.

title: bavarian party dip
directions: Saute the onions 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and drain.
Mix braunschweiger with the cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in onion and pepper.
Serve as dip for veggies or as a spread on crackers or party rye.

title: golden potato soup
directions: Boil all veggies until tender.
Add milk and thicken with flour.
Lastly, add cheese, but do not boil after adding cheese. You may add more milk, if needed.
Serves 35.

title: chocolate raspberry cheesecake(diabetic)
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add cottage cheese and fruit spread; blend until smooth.
Add pudding mix; blend until smooth.
Pour pudding mixture into large bowl.
Gently stir in the cool whip. Pour into 8 inch pie plate.
Smooth top.
Sprinkle with chocolate. Freeze until firm, approximately 6 hours.
Remove cheesecake from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Top with raspberries.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Place zucchini, onions and salt in a large bowl.
Mix the ingredients well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next day, place mixture in a fine sieve; drain well, rinse under cold water and drain again for 1 hour.
Place zucchini mixture in heavy soup pot with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate, covered.
Will keep for up to 3 to 4 weeks.
Yield: 5 cups.
Good on hot dogs and sandwiches.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Let bread dough rise according to directions.
Roll out to a rectangular piece.
Combine egg, parsley, oregano, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Spread onto dough.
Top with pepperoni and cheese slices.
(Sometimes I also add slices of green pepper and onions.) Roll up dough, starting at long end and pinching ends.
Brush the roll with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes on jelly roll pan.

title: pineapple in a cloud
directions: Cut or tear cake into little pieces.
Mix pudding and juice until thick.
Add crushed pineapple and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cake with mix, cake, mix and cake.

title: bread pudding(an 1880 recipe)
directions: Place crumbs in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Place baking dish in pan of water. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean, approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put sugar and syrup in a heavy saucepan.
Cook to boiling point and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and stir.
Stir in cereal and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Grease 8-inch baking dish.
Spread margarine on bread slices. Arrange 4 slices of bread in dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Repeat, making 2 more layers. In medium bowl with whisk, beat milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and eggs until well mixed.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Fill 1 gallon glass jar almost full with sliced cucumbers and 3 or 4 sliced onions.
Heat together and cool all other ingredients.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Squeeze out excess water.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: pileau(pearl o)
directions: You could also use ham, shrimp or sausage.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add flour; mix well.
Blend in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.

title: candied fruit drops
directions: Beat sugar, oleo, eggs and milk.
Stir in flour sifted with soda.
Add nuts and fruit.
Mix well. Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop by spoonful on baking sheet.
Bake about 400° for 10 minutes.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Mix well together in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Gradually add cornmeal and stir until mushy. Allow mixture to cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add salt, butter, beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased pan or spoon mixture by the spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: stir-fried succotash
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook lima beans as directed on package; drain.
Heat wok or large skillet until hot. Add bacon drippings and vegetable oil; rotate to coat.
Add onions and corn; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add lima beans, tomatoes and okra; stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth, sugar, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
Cover; continue cooking a few minutes.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple cake #1
directions: Generously grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.
Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Pour one-third of the batter into prepared pan; layer half of the apples and half of the cinnamon mixture on top of batter.
Evenly spread the remaining batter over this and layer the rest of the apples and cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut fiber crunch
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream together sugars and margarine.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown but not set.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place broth, water, tomatoes, basil, oregano and pepper in a 4-quart saucepan; cover and bring to a boil.

title: noel nut balls
directions: Stir first 2 ingredients together.
Add other ingredients. Blend well (dough is somewhat crumbly).
Mold into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: american key lime pie
directions: Thoroughly mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in saucepan. Beat together egg yolks, lime juice and water; stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat just until mixture comes to boil.
Remove from heat, stir in grated peel.
Add food coloring sparingly to tint pale green.
Chill; stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: walnut spread
directions: Beat cream cheese with milk.
Blend in walnuts.

title: ratatouille(even veggie haters like this!)
directions: Cube and salt eggplant.
Set aside.
Slice or chop onion, pepper, zucchini and tomatoes.
Saute all vegetables in oil, cook thoroughly.
Drain water from eggplant.
Add to other vegetables. Add basil, thyme and stock.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add romano cheese just before serving.
For a French variation add Polish sausage.

title: taco salad stack-ups
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Combine with chili seasoning, water, tomato sauce, kidney beans, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Combine cheese, soup and taco sauce in saucepan.
Heat until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes, ground beef mixture and cheese sauce on tortillas.
Garnish with sour cream. Yield:
10 servings.

title: lemon macaroon tartlets
directions: Place egg in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, and lemon rind in a saucepan; stir well.
Gradually add water and lemon juice; stir with a wire whisk until blended.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir one fourth of hot lemon mixture into egg; add to remaining lemon mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat 1 minute or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into a bowl; stir in food coloring, if desired.
Place plastic wrap on surface, and chill.
Spoon 1 Tbsp. plus 1 tsp. lemon mixture into each Macaroon Tart Shell.
Top each with 2 tsp. whipped topping, and sprinkle with 1/2 tsp. toasted coconut.
Yield 1 dozen.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat until light.
Add egg and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Cover with Crumb Topping.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.

In small microwave bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk. Microwave at High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla; spread into pan.
In small microwave bowl, add remaining sweetened condensed milk and semi-sweet chocolate chips and microwave 1 to 1 1/2 minutes and stir after
1 minute or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla and spread over your peanut butter layer.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares and store in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 4 dozen pieces.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can fried onions, reserving other half for topping.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, for an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
In another bowl, combine the egg, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Pour batter into a greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Use a toothpick to test for doneness. Remove pan to a rack.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Invert onto a breadboard or platter.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Serves 6.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut the steak into 1-inch cubes.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray, and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak; cook 4 minutes or until steak loses its pink color.
Remove steak from skillet; drain and set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple and fruit salad.
Mix pudding and pineapple juice until smooth.
Mix fruit.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: onion-flavored rice mix(special flavor for a side dish or casserole)
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until evenly distributed.
Put about 1 1/3 cups mixture each into three 1-pint airtight containers.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 to 8 months.
Makes about 4 cups of Onion-Flavored Rice Mix.

title: hot peppers in sauce
directions: Note:
Use rubber gloves while handling peppers.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in water 20 to 30 minutes until plump.
Drain raisins and pour liquid into measuring cup, adding enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, then raisin liquid.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture, then add oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until light brown at 400°.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: charles dickens' fish and chips
directions: Dredge 1 1/2 pound flounder in small amount of flour.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl until smooth.
Heat oil or shortening for deep frying (350°).
Dip fish into batter and lower into hot oil.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.

title: spinach-rice soup
directions: Bring broth and spinach to a full boil in medium saucepan. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Season with pepper and nutmeg.
Makes 3 servings.
May be doubled.

title: baked fish
directions: Have the market scale the fish; split down the middle and remove the center bone.
Wash well and add the juice of 1 lemon outside and in the cavity.
Add the next four ingredients.
Set into fridge for 2 to 4 hours.

title: cranberry sauce for chicken or pork
directions: Combine ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Simmer on medium heat. Roast pork at 325° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Halfway through, reduce heat to 175°.
Baste with sauce every 15 minutes.
Spread excess sauce on platter and put the roast on top.

title: deep dish pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line bottom of pie crust with Mozzarella cheese slices; reserve rest.
Using 1/2 of pepperoni, mix rest together.
Put in pie shells.
Put reserved Mozzarella slices and rest of pepperoni on top.
Bake for 40 minutes or until crust is brown and cheese melted.
Can add mushrooms, green peppers, onions and other pizza topping to taste.

title: very easy pie crust
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Add Wesson oil and cold milk together.
Stir lightly.
Round up dough.
Place half between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Roll gently until circle reaches edge of paper.
Peel off top paper and pick up crust and bottom paper; turn over onto pie plate.
Carefully remove paper.
Fill and add top crust, sealing edges with a fork.
Make slit in top crust for air to escape.
Bake as pie recipe calls for.

title: fish and rice(lebanese dish)
directions: In a large skillet place oil and fry the fish.
Remove the fish when done, and in the same oil, add the onions.
Fry until tender but not brown.
Again in the same oil, fry the pine nuts until brown.
Remove.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: In a covered saucepan, simmer chicken in salted water, enough water to cover for 20 minutes; drain.
In a bowl, combine pancake mix and salt; stir in water.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Dip chicken in batter.
Let excess batter drain off into bowl.
In heavy skillet, deep fry a few pieces of chicken at a time until golden brown.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown ground beef or ground turkey, onion and garlic in Dutch oven until meat is no longer pink.
Add barley and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook simmering 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Roll each biscuit flat.
Place apple filling in each biscuit and gather biscuit on top.
Roll in butter and set in pan.
Melt 1 cup sugar in 1 cup warm water.
Pour between dumplings (they will float). Sprinkle a lot of cinnamon and sugar on each dumpling.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: far east chicken
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions, omitting butter and salt.
Cut chicken into 1 1/2 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet.
Add chicken and garlic salt.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and soy sauce.
Cover and cook until zucchini is crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine water and cornstarch; add to skillet. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture is thickened and clear, 2 minutes.
Stir onion into hot cooked rice.
Serve chicken mixture over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nestle candy shop pizza(makes about 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12 to 14-inch pizza pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: zucchini cheddar bake
directions: Boil the zucchini in salted water and mash it coarsely.
Saute the onion in butter.
Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole; sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
tags: Italian style bread crumbs and additional

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake 36 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: icebox cookies*
directions: Cream sugars, shortening, vanilla and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mold into 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 1 hour.
Slice and bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This can be baked in an oblong baking dish or loaf pan.

title: microwave herb bread
directions: Place butter and spices in a glass custard cup; heat on full power 1 minute.
Mix thoroughly.
Slice bread crosswise in 1/2-inch slices, being careful not to slice through bottom crust. Brush herb spread on slices.
Wrap in paper toweling and place in bread basket.
Heat herb bread on roast for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: apricot delight
directions: Prepare jello and let set.
Add pineapple and bananas.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers in thin, round slices and place in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for about 30 minutes. Squeeze out excess moisture.

title: yummy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Bake 1 hour.

title: nanny's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Sift salt and soda in with flour.
Add to mixture.
Add chocolate bits last.
Place in refrigerator overnight or until well chilled. Bake in a 350° oven.
Makes about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: sweet potato banana custards
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sweet potatoes and bananas. Add milk; mix well.
Stir in brown sugar, eggs and salt until well blended.
Spray eight 1/2-inch ramekins, souffle dishes or 6 ounce custard cups with nonstick spray coating.
Divide mixture evenly among the ramekins or cups.
Sprinkle raisins in each cup. Arrange ramekins or cups on a baking sheet.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of each.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 35 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Brown the beef; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and sugar. Press biscuits into ungreased muffin pan.
Fill the depression with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: janhagel cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar; blend well.
Add egg yolk; blend well.
Stir in flour and cinnamon.
Press mixture into a greased wax paper-lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place this in Pammed 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish. Top with potato tots.
Combine soup with milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake 25 minutes before adding cheese.

title: pastry for fried apple pies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Divide the dough into 8-10 pieces.
Place one piece at a time between 2 sheets of wax paper and roll into a circle.
Place apple mixture in the center of dough.
Dip finger in water and spread on bottom half of pastry. Fold other half over and crimp with fork.
The water seals pastry and prevents the filling from cooking out.
Place pies in cooking oil and fry until brown.
Turn and brown second side.
Remove and place on paper towel to cool.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Cook wheel noodles. Add meat and onions to drained noodles.
Add pepperoni, green pepper and mushrooms.
Then add spaghetti sauce and cheese.
Stir together and put in baking dish or cake pan (sprayed).
Cover with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato yummies
directions: Spread potatoes out in pan and sprinkle with salt.
Mix next 5 ingredients and put on top of potatoes.
Spread melted butter on top.
Sprinkle crumbled cornflakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: jello blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. Mix well and refrigerate until firm.

title: baked corn and tomatoes
directions: Mix seasonings with corn and tomatoes.
Pour all into a greased baking dish.
Spread bread crumbs over the top.
Dot them with the butter or margarine.
Bake in a 350° to 400° oven for 30 minutes.
A good way to use leftover corn or tomatoes.

title: apple cider biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Stir 3/4 cup cider into mixture until soft dough forms that leaves the side of the bowl.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Put sugar, milk and butter in microwave and cook on High for 20 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and marshmallow and stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Peanut butter may be used instead of chocolate chips.

title: grated potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put all ingredients into blender container in order listed; cover and run on speed 6 (or high) just until all potatoes go through the blades (do not overblend).
Pour into casserole and bake for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southwest ruffle salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cilantro, milk, lime juice, jalapeno pepper and salt.
Add pasta, tomatoes, yellow bell pepper, zucchini and green onions; toss to coat well. Cover; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar; mix well.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into graham cracker crust. Place in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter dish, sprinkle crumbs for crust.
Mix all ingredients into pan.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry bars(student favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling, extract and beaten eggs.
Gently stir by hand (preferably with a wooden spoon) until well mixed.
Pour onto pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).

title: special pennsylvania dutch sauce
directions: Combine fat, hamburger, onion and water.
Make sure all ingredients are chopped fine.
Simmer a half hour.
Add salt, pepper and chili powder; simmer another half hour.

title: baked oysters(appetizer)
directions: Combine in glass 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Broil for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers or toast rounds.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put sherbet in a punch bowl.
Pour chilled juice and ginger ale over sherbet.
Mix together.

title: swedish lasagna
directions: Saute oil, onion and meat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, oregano, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles; drain and cover with cold water.
Add 1 tablespoon salad oil.
Arrange 1/3 meat sauce, single layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Repeat until 3 layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Top with remaining Pepperidge Farm.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie roll on pizza pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and nuts.
Spread on cookie.
Combine jello, 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and water in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Stir constantly once it starts boiling.
Let cool.
Combine fruit with jello mixture.
Spread on cookie.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, syrup, butter, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Spread nuts over bottom of crust.
Pour in pie filling.
Bake at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat milk and peanut butter smooth. Add egg, Bisquick and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes.
When they come out of oven, immediately put chocolate Kiss on top and push it in.

title: st. gregory's abbey altar bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add yeast to warm water and mix until dissolved.
Measure honey into water.
Stir until dissolved. Measure olive oil into water.
Stir for a few seconds to break it up, but it won't emulsify much.
Stir in the salt.
Add unsifted flour and mix.
The dough will become somewhat stiff.
Add another tablespoon of warm water if needed.
Take a ball of raw dough and roll it out to 1/4-inch thick and 4 1/2-inches across.
Make about 5 mini loaves.
Place on oiled cookie sheet and let rise for 10 to 15 minutes on top of the oven.
Then bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana whip dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Chop graham crackers.
Pat into bottom of spring-form pan.
Mix pudding and sour cream.
Add Cool Whip.
Put half pudding mixture on top of graham crackers.
Slice all three bananas and put on top of pudding mixture.
Put rest of pudding mixture on top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all in a large bowl.
Chill 1 hour.
Form into a ball. Have hands wet and roll in chopped nuts and parsley flakes.

title: beggar's purses
directions: In large bowl, mix together the cilantro, sausage, red pepper flakes and five spice powder.
Heat the oil in a large skillet and brown the gingerroot and garlic until fragrant and golden.
Add sausage and saute until cooked.
Drain the sausage mixture; arrange a few of the wonton skins on a clean surface.
Use only one skin at a time.
Keep the others covered with a damp towel. Spoon 1 or 2 tablespoons of the sausage mixture onto each skin. Crimp the edges and tie with a length of green onion.
Pierce the bottom of each wonton with a skewer.
In a deep pot, heat about 2 inches of oil.
When the oil is hot enough, drop the wonton into it.
Cook until light and crispy, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Transfer to a paper towel to drain.
Keep warm as you cook others.
Serve immediately with red hot chili only, spicey mustard, honey or soy sauce.

title: fruit and vegetable salad
directions: Drain pineapple, save juice. Mix jello according to the box using the pineapple juices as part of the cold water. Allow to chill about 30 minutes. Add a capful or 1/2 tsp. vinegar.

title: taco burgers
directions: Brown beef until crumbly; drain off fat.
Add tomatoes and seasoning mix.
Stir well, breaking up large pieces of tomatoes. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon over toasted buns.
Sprinkle with cheese and lettuce.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast, mushroom soup and water into roasting pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Put carrots, celery, onions, and potatoes into roasting pan.
Bake for another 2 hours. Add more water if needed.

title: sugar free apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry and set aside in pie plate.
Mix apples, apple juice, flour and spice.
Stir until all apples are well coated. Add lemon juice and stir.
Taste one piece of apple to check for spice.
Pour into pie plate.
Place pastry on top.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
This tastes delicious.
Just like a regular apple pie but without the sugar.

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Fry pepperoni until edges curl.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and oregano; cook 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Toss with spaghetti and combined cheeses.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Wrap chicken breast with sandwich ham and then wrap with sliced bacon.
Place in baking dish.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream. Spread over chicken. Seal with foil.
Marinate overnight or for several hours.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
The last 15 minutes, uncover and add grated cheese, if desired.
Melt.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape in melon size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix together chopped pecans, flour and soft butter.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: herb chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Brush evenly on top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until tender and browned.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and peanut butter with hands or spoon.
Then roll in graham cracker crumbs.

title: ultimate double chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir just until well blended.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining butter.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in the pecans and chocolate chunks.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan. Yields 3 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix ingredients.
Cut celery into cubes/slices and fill with crab meat.
Serve remaining crab meat with crackers.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until well blended. Refrigerate several hours before serving to allow flavors to develop.

title: venison roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with seasoning.
Top with bacon and onions. Wrap in tin foil; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Put water in bottom of pan.

title: "anything goes into" meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, salt, pepper, dry mustard, celery salt, nutmeg, chopped onion, egg, milk and ground beef.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix water, pickle juice and brown sugar.
Put around meat.
Rub catsup on meat and put pineapple on top.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Cream
with mixer.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add apples with 2 tablespoons of buttermilk.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350°.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, butter, buttermilk and soda. Combine with flour and 1 cup jam.
Add cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nuts.
Bake until a toothpick comes out clean.
You may use any frost you care for.

title: crispy chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: In a pie plate, dip chicken into egg; coat with bread crumbs. In a skillet over medium-low heat, in hot oil, cook chicken until browned on both sides and no longer pink.
Keep warm.
In same skillet over low heat, combine soup, milk and water.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon soup mixture over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients to a stiff dough.
Roll very thin; let rest 20 minutes.
Roll loosely; slice 1/4-inch wide.
Unroll and cut into desired lengths.
Dry 2 hours.
Drop into boiling liquid. Cook, uncovered, for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: large savory macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix together macaroni, bread crumbs, cheese (can also use some grated yellow Cheddar cheese with sharp cheese), minced onion, salt and pepper.
Bacon bits or sweet red pepper can also be added to this mixture.

title: monterey soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine sausage, pinto beans, corn, garbanzo, hash browns, tomatoes, salsa, and cumin.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook for about 30 minutes or until garbanzos are fork tender.
Add water, as needed.
Stir in cheese.

title: ritzy corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, green beans, soup, sour cream, salt, onion, green pepper and celery in a bowl; mix well.
Spray a 9 x 13 inch microwave-safe casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour in vegetable mixture.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs together in bowl.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Microwave on high for 9 minutes, turning every 3 minutes.
You can also bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Remove contents of crabmeat from can.
Separate into pieces; remove thin cartilage.
Drain crabmeat; add to sauce and heat over low heat.
Add sherry wine and stir constantly for a few minutes. Turn into well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler to brown.
Serve at once.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan the jello and water until dissolved. Add undrained pineapple and blueberry filling.
Stir and let set.

title: tropical fruit parfaits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut in a single layer on an ungreased sheet pan.
Toast coconut in oven 5 to 10 minutes or until light brown and crisp.
Peel and slice kiwi fruit.
In a small bowl, stir kiwi slices with pineapple chunks and mandarin oranges.
Spoon 1/3 cup yogurt into four parfait glasses. Sprinkle 1/4 cup granola over yogurt; spoon in 2 tablespoons fruit mixture.
Repeat once and top with a sprinkling of toasted coconut.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggplant
directions: Slice it real thin and put it in flour or cornmeal or an egg batter.
Fry it in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: sesame chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken crosswise into 1/2-inch wide strips.
In large bowl, combine sour cream, lemon juice, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Add chicken to sour cream mixture; coat chicken well.
Cover; refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: oatmeal, cornflake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg and oil to mixture and mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and add to butter mixture, then add 1 teaspoon each of the following to the mixture:
soda, salt and vanilla.
Form into balls the size of a walnut and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 minutes if crispy cookies are desired.
For chewy cookies, cut back time to 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet before storing.
These are very crisp and store well.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Should chill overnight for best flavor.
Great on celery sticks or crackers.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer; will be pretty thick.
Rub Bundt pan really good with butter or butter flavored Crisco and sprinkle real good with granulated sugar.
Bake 1 hour or until cake is done.
Ovens vary so use own judgment.

title: sara nell's blueberry muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly with fork.
Stir in milk and corn oil.
Sift together and add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin cups, 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 400° oven.
Yield: 12 medium muffins.

title: grandmom's sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
May add a little flour on hands and dough to make it easy to work.
Squeeze into small balls about the size of a pingpong ball.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Biscuits are done when bottoms are beginning to brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Blend oleo, cream cheese and flour together. Chill 1 hour.

title: saltine toffee
directions: Simple toffee made with ingredients you probably have in your pantry right now.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put milk in a double boiler.
Beat eggs and sugar until mixed, then add hot milk, a cup at a time, and beat.
Pour all back into rest of hot milk and cook until it coats the spoon. Add vanilla and chill.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix fruit and dressing.
Fold in whipping cream.
Allow to cool 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: zucchini turkey sausage casserole
directions: Saute and drain the sausage.
Mix in 1 tablespoon flour and place in the bottom of a casserole dish (9 x 1 4-inch or 1 1/2-quart).
In a skillet, place margarine.
Over low heat, partially cook, but do not brown, the zucchini and chopped onion. Mix 4 tablespoons of the flour into vegetables.
Place 1/2 of vegetable mixture over the sausage; reserve the remainder.
Add cottage cheese as the next layer.
Mix together the Parmesan cheese, eggs and garlic salt.
Place on top of cottage cheese, then add a layer of the remaining zucchini mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with the grated cheese; bake 2 more minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: cola pot roast
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place roast in large dutch oven.
Pour ingredients over roast.
Cover and cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; place in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Set aside.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together.
Bake in muffin tin sprayed with Pam at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Cover mushrooms with water.
Add sliced onion and salt.
Boil slowly for 1/2 hour.
Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add remainder of mushrooms, chopped.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add flour and milk to make a smooth, thick sauce.
Add mushroom liquid and mushrooms, rubbed through a sieve.
Just before serving, add paprika and cream.

title: baker's frosting
