directions: This will keep in covered container in refrigerator.

title: mexican candy
directions: Toast pecans (250° for 20 minutes). Mix sugar, Milnot, syrup, butter and salt. Bring to a boil and boil for exactly 3 minutes. Add vanilla and cool. Beat until creamy. Add nuts and pour into a buttered pan.
Cool. Cut into small pieces.

title: best bran muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
Make a well in the center.
Combine the egg, oil, molasses, buttermilk and pineapple with juice.
Pour into well; mix until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in nuts, dates, or raisins.
Fill 18 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to directions.
Melt the stick of margarine in a saucepan.
Add flour until mixture thickens.
This could take more or less than the two tablespoons of flour.
Add approximately four cups of milk.
When this mixture becomes hot, not boiling, add the pound of Velveeta (cut into pieces; the smaller the pieces the quicker the cheese will melt into a sauce). Add salt according to taste.
Stir this mixture constantly or it will scorch.

title: hot vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco mix with 1/2 cup water and simmer.
Add all other ingredients.
Slow cook 1 hour.

title: ruth's cranberry cookies
directions: Cream together the eggs, brown sugar, oleo and orange peel. Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately with the mixed milk and vanilla.
Stir in the cranberries and nuts and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: In mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing.
Mix until smooth.
Slice a thin slice off tops of tomatoes and carefully remove insides.
Invert on paper towel to drain.
Fill with cream cheese mixture.
Serve on a bed of alfalfa sprouts, if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: grandpa's perfect pound cake
directions: Beat butter with sugar for 5 minutes at low speed.
Add egg yolks; beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Beat egg whites 2 minutes at high speed with same beater, then beat creamed mixture 5 minutes longer at low speed.
Sift 5 1/2 cups flour and baking powder together.
Beat 1/3 of flour into bowl at low speed.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Beat in 1/3 of flour until blended.
Add egg whites; beat until smooth.
Reserve 1/4 cup flour.
Add remaining flour to bowl; increase speed to medium and beat for 5 minutes more.
Add vanilla and grated lemon rind.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.

title: golden glazed chicken
directions: Combine soup mix, preserves and water.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Top with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn once.
Serve on hot rice.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: In saucepan, place pineapple, water, sugar and gelatin.
Cook until thickened.
Let cool.
Take half of the cake and break into small pieces.
Line glass dish with pieces of cake.
Add half of Cool Whip, coconut and pecans.
Add half of pineapple mixture. Layer again.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg. Roll in bread crumb mixture. Place in greased baking dish. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: valentine red punch
directions: In large pitcher, combine punch and grapefruit juice; mix well.
Slowly stir in orange soda.
Add ice.
Pour into glasses. Garnish with orange or lime slices; if desired.
Makes about 2 quarts or enough for eight 8-ounce servings.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Blend in blender 3 minutes or beat with beater until smooth. Delicious on any tossed salad.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with small amount of onion; drain well.
Mix sugar and vinegar well.
Add mustard, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to browned hamburger and cook slowly on low for 1/2 hour.
Fast, easy and delicious.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Add egg yolk and 1/4 cup milk; mix well.
Stir in rest of milk and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Cool.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into freezer tray.
Freeze until almost firm.
Turn into mixing bowl and beat until creamy.
Add egg whites and beat until doubled in volume.
Fold in berries.
Refreeze.
Makes 8 servings.

title: polynesian shrimp grilled kabobs
directions: Peel and cut up pineapple in large chunks.
Seed and cut up green peppers in large chunks.
Peel and cut up onion into large chunks.
Take half of this mixture and mix coarsely in food processor or blender.
Set aside.

title: spicey snack mix
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels, Cheez-Its, and peanuts together.
Melt butter and mix in seasonings.
Pour over cereal mix.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: chicken milano
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Meanwhile, remove skin and bones from chicken breasts; cut breast meat into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter or oleo, cook onion and garlic until onion is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken chunks and cook until slightly browned on all sides; stir frequently.
Stir in undiluted tomato soup and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
To serve, spoon chicken mixture over rice in deep platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel nut crunch
directions: Melt butter.
Add Karo and sugar.
Cook until sugar melts. Pour over cereal until well coated.
Pour on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil; stir to wet mixture. Do not beat.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Do not beat.
Put in 3 greased and floured pans.
Cook at 350° for about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: spicy texas chili
directions: Trim off excess fat from beef.
Cut meat off bone into chunks. Put meat and bone into a 4 to 5-quart heavy metal pan, along with 1/2 cup water.
Cover; cook over medium-high heat until meat releases juices and turns gray, about 30 minutes.
Uncover; cook juices away, then turn meat in rendered fat until well browned on all sides, 30 minutes more.
Lift out meat; set aside.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Run Oreo cookies through a blender or food processor.
Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine and beat sugar, flour, syrup and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg is added. Add vanilla and lemon juice and beat vigorously until bubbly.
Pour over pecans in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° or 325° until pie shakes like jello. I double the recipe. Use one 10-inch and one 9-inch pie plate and a quart of pecans.

title: burger skillet
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and milk.
Make into meat balls.
In large skillet, fry meat balls until brown; drain. To meat balls, add the package of spaghetti sauce mix and 2 cups water.
Simmer 15 minutes, adding water if needed.
Cut green pepper, onion, carrots and potatoes into chunks.
Add to meat balls and sauce.
Add tomatoes (and more water, if needed).
Heat until vegetables are tender.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and orange pieces.
Add cottage cheese and stir. Pour in dry powdered jello and mix well. Stir in topping.
This sets quickly and lasts for days. Can be frozen.
This can also be served in sherbet glasses as a dessert.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl. Pour batter into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: nutty muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Fill greased muffin pan cups 1/2 full with batter.
Bake in a preheated 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6.

title: chop suey cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in milk.
Add flour and milk alternately to mixture and blend well. Add other ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar, butter and eggs thoroughly.
Blend the dry ingredients; stir in.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chopped onion and saute.
Add paprika.
Slowly add stock.
Simmer, then add skinned chicken. Simmer covered 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add flour and sour cream or yogurt or half and half.
Stir into chicken stock 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles.

title: crunchy cheese snacks
directions: Combine
first
8 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Add
butter;
stir
with
a
fork
until
well blended. Sprinkle water evenly over; stir with a fork until dough forms a ball.

title: buns
directions: Combine yeast and water. Set aside. Mix remaining ingredients, except the flour. Add yeast mixture. Mix and add flour a little at a time by stirring until it gets too stiff. Then knead by hand until you have a soft smooth dough. Put in a greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk. Knead down and form roll into desired size rolls. Place on greased baking sheets. Let rise until double in bulk. Bake in 350° oven until rolls are golden brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat milk, rice, sugar and salt just to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally, until rice is very tender.
In small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in small amount of hot rice mixture.
Slowly pour egg mixture back into rice, stirring rapidly to prevent lumping.
Add raisins, if desired, stirring constantly for about 5 minutes.
Do not boil, or mixture will curdle.
Add vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all together; put in casserole dish.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove and put crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour oil into deep skillet to depth of 1-inch.
Fill pan no more than 1/3 full.
Heat to 375°.
Funnel batter into hot oil (about 1/4 cup of batter).
Fry, turning over after 2 minutes or golden brown. Drain and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: candied yams
directions: Place sliced sweet potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Combine sugar, spices, margarine and flour.
Sprinkle over top of sweet potatoes.
Pour the water in corners.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Enjoy.

title: country fair soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water; stir in remaining 1 cup water.
Mix
salt with 4 cups flour in large bowl.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add
enough
additional flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 10 minutes or until dough feels elastic.
Round dough
into
ball. Place
in lightly greased bowl, turning to coat
dough.
Cover; let
rise in warm place until doubled in bulk,
about
45 minutes. Pinch off small amount of dough and roll
between
hands to form coil about 20 inches long and 1/4 inch
in
diameter.
Shape
coil as pretzel.
(Make a loop by carefully
picking
up
ends and forming a loop in the center; bring left end over to the right and right end under the left, forming a
twist
at top of loop.
Turn the ends over and back onto loop, pressing ends against sides.) Repeat with remaining dough.
Dissolve
baking
soda
in
water and bring to a boil. Drop one
pretzel
at a time into boiling water and let boil 1 minute
or
until
pretzel
floats.
Remove; drain.
Place on buttered
baking
sheets.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 475°
for
12 minutes or until golden brown.
Place on rack to cool.
The treat is yours.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water in a pot; boil for 5 minutes.
Add beets and toss well.
Let stand 30 minutes or more. Just before serving, add oleo and reheat to boiling point.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in roasting pan.
Pour liquid smoke over, coating sides.
Sprinkle with onion salt, garlic salt and celery salt.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Pour barbecue sauce over brisket.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 5 hours.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: italian chicken soup(low fat - low calorie)
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan; stir-fry chicken pieces until lightly browned. Add onion, celery and garlic; cook and stir until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in basil, pepper, water, broth and tomatoes; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in corn and vermicelli. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated and vermicelli is tender. Garnish each serving with parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Put broccoli in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix rice and water and let set until rice is done.
Mix all ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oats and apple trail bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and stir to blend.
Press mixture into an ungreased 9-inch square cake pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes and cut into bars while still warm.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Cut chicken into chunks and place in a 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch Pam sprayed pan.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread on chicken.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Combine crumbs and melted oleo and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix baking soda and sugar together.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with soda and sugar.
Make small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame chicken kabob
directions: Note:
You will need 8 (6-inch) skewers, soaked in water.

title: easy 7-minute frosting
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in a double boiler. Cook and beat 7 minutes. Remove from heat and cool.
(Delicious on chocolate cake!)

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Combine mushroom soup, mushrooms, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot-squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots, and onions in boiling water until partially
done.
Drain;
place
in casserole dish and add 1/2 cup melted
butter,
salt
and
pepper.
Cream together cream cheese and
cream
of mushroom soup.
Spread over vegetables. Spread crackers
over
soup.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for twenty minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Roll crumbs very fine; put in bowl.
Add milk, sugar, melted butter, eggs, chopped apples, raisins, pineapple and flavor.
Mix well after each ingredient; blend all together.
Pour in a baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until well set.

title: low calorie soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until tender (1 to 2 hours).
You can add carrots and green beans, too.

title: gazpacho
directions: Mix two parts to 1 part vinegar and oil, 1 tablespoon water, 2/3 cup safflower oil, 1/3 cup vinegar.

title: taco soup(use crock-pot)
directions: Brown meat; add onion and taco mix.
Add other ingredients to crock-pot.
Add meat mixture and cook slow 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with corn chips.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: Place yeast, water and 1 tablespoon sugar in a large bowl; set aside.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Heat buttermilk on low heat until lukewarm.
Combine with yeast mixture.
Add remaining sugar and corn oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, 2 cups at a time; blend.
Let stand for 10 minutes; knead 5 minutes. Form into rolls; place on greased pans.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 2 to 3 dozen.

title: beth's coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients, except pie filling.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine all ingredients. Bake in a serving dish or a fondue dish. Keep warm when serving. Accompany with crusty French bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and wine together.
Save about a cup for later.
Mix rest with rice in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put raw chicken on top.
Top with sauteed mushrooms.
Put reserved 1 cup sauce on top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: creamed cabbage au gratin
directions: Make toasted bread into crumbs by dropping pieces into blender at high speed.
Mix with 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Add cabbage and cook over high heat for 8 minutes; drain.
Place in lightly buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare white sauce by melting margarine over medium heat; add flour and allow to bubble for 1 minute.
Slowly add milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Stir until thickened and smooth.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with cheese, crumbs and bacon. Bake uncovered at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Serves 6.

title: mock crab cakes(or how to use more zucchini)
directions: Combine and mix all of the ingredients.
Form into 3-inch patties, 1/2-inch thick.
Saute in oil until nicely browned.

title: ugly cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well and spread in slightly greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, salt, egg and 1/2 cup sugar until smooth.
Drop by spoonful over batter and marbleize.
Sprinkle small package chocolate chips over mixture and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, salt and vinegar until thickened.
Add all ingredients at least 4 hours before serving.
Will keep 2 weeks. Stir before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cut avocados in half, working around the pit. Separate the two halves. Remove pit and scoop out the avocado flesh with a spoon. Wedge the avocados and pile them in the center of a large platter. Seed and wedge the tomatoes and arrange them around the avocados. Spread sliced onion over the platter. Sprinkle the cilantro over all the vegetables. Squeeze the juice from both limes over all. Then season with coarse salt. Drizzle platter with oil, and serve.

title: chicken rice
directions: Place chicken in dish.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spread soup over chicken and broth.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: no time red velvet cake
directions: Mix all
together.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Use regular red velvet cake icing to frost.

title: sue's chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and melted chocolate; beat well.
Stir in the vanilla, milk, nuts, flour and salt.
Chill 1 hour.

title: sausage and hash brown casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Combine with other ingredients. Bake in 1 3/4-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. If desired, top with mixture of 1/3 cup butter and 1 cup cornflakes (crushed) before baking.

title: scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Blend or sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in finely the shortening; add currants or raisins. Combine egg and milk; add to dry ingredients. Stir lightly with a fork to make a soft dough. Turn dough onto a light floured surface and knead gently 8 to 10 times. Divide dough into two parts; roll each into 6-inch circle. Place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Score each into quarters. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. This makes 8 scones.

title: cream cheese burritos
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas.
Spread a thin layer on a tortilla and roll it up.
Repeat until all tortillas have been rolled.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Cut into 1-inch sections to serve.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Blend well the sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add margarine and eggs.
Blend well.
Add rhubarb.
Place into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or at 300° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325° until lightly browned but soft.
These cookies puff up at first, then flatten out with crinkled tops.
Serves 5 dozen.

title: lebkuchen(german)
directions: Heat honey to boiling in a small saucepan; cook in large bowl about 30 minutes.
Stir in sugar, lemon juice and egg; blend well. Combine sifted flour with spices and soda.
Stir in honey mixture 1/3 at a time.
Add lemon peel and almonds.
Dough will be stiff but sticky.
Wrap in foil or transparent wrap, refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: cream cheese and dried beef spread
directions: Stir cream cheese just until it gets relatively easy to stir. Add Worcestershire sauce and blend.
Dump in dried beef and stir until blended.
Add onion and stir.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Serve with Waverly Wafers, Ritz crackers or any other slightly sweet, buttery tasting crackers.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled.
Also may be made several days in advance and kept refrigerated, just keep tightly wrapped.

title: becky's mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread on plate and layer ingredients in order given above.
May add shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: easy sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onion.
Add soup, water and rice. Place in baking dish and bake one hour at 350°.

title: lemon spice tea
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, honey, 1 lemon slice and stick cinnamon.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add tea bags.
Cover and steep for 4 minutes.
Remove tea bags, cinnamon and lemon slices.
Pour tea into 4 cups.
Serve hot.
Garnish with additional lemon slices, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer until fluffy.
This makes plenty for layer cake.
Use half this recipe for 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Cover with chow mein noodles and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: dumplings
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend eggs, milk and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons in boiling broth or water. Cover and cook for 20 minutes.

title: curry-cajun spiced chicken
directions: In a 3-quart rectangular baking dish, combine honey, water, mustard, melted margarine or butter, Cajun seasoning, curry powder, lemon juice and garlic.
Mix well.
Add chicken breasts (halves), turning to coat.
Arrange in a single layer. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Serve chicken with pan drippings with hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: "colcannon"(potatoes and cabbage)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Return potatoes to saucepan and mash to puree.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: pink stuff
directions: Put all
ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add milk and beat more.
Add dry ingredients; mix to smooth.
Bake on hot lightly greased griddle. Makes 12 to 14 average size.

title: cooked custard
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add milk.
Cook a little then add beaten egg yolks and finish cooking with vanilla.
Good for banana cream pie!

title: mock enchilada casserole
directions: Mix liquid, soup and milk; add cut up pieces of cheese and cook over slow heat until cheese melts.
Add green chilies.
Pour layer of liquid and layer of tortillas until all used.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix together in a saucepan the jello and crushed pineapple in natural juice.
Bring to a boil; simmer 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and baby apricots.
Fold into cooled jello mixture and then fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a jello mold.
Chill until firm.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift flour; fix a place in center and add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at the degree you bake your biscuits.

title: country ham
directions: To remove salt, soak ham completely covered in cold water for 24 hours; drain.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in oven bag; place in a roasting pan at least 2 inches deep.
Scrub ham in warm water with a stiff brush; rinse well.
Place ham in a bag.
Add 4 cups water.
Close bag with nylon tie; cut six 1/2-inch slits in top.
Through slit in bag, puncture the thickest part of the ham with a knife.
Insert meat thermometer into ham, not touching bone.
Bake until meat thermometer reads 160°, 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours.
Let stand in bag 15 minutes.
Trim skin and fat from ham.

title: oriental hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add rice.
Watch close and stir often.
Put in casserole and saute (brown a little in butter) the celery and onion.
Add to the hamburger and rice.
Add the soup, soy sauce and water.
Mix well.
Drain bean sprouts and add to casserole. Toss lightly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: mushroom-broccoli salad
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Cut in bite-size pieces.
Clean broccoli. Cut in bite-size flowerets.
Mix all remaining ingredients together well.
Pour over mushrooms and broccoli pieces.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours.

title: beef burgundy stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef in oil.
Pour off fat, add broth, wine, tomatoes, bay leaf, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and mushrooms and cook 30 minutes more.
Gradually blend water with cornstarch and slowly stir into sauce.
Cook, stirring, until thickens.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread one can chicken a la King in oblong casserole dish. Place 2 to 3 tablespoons grated cheese down center of tortilla; sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons chopped onion.
Roll tortilla up to form enchilada.
Place seam side down on a la King in dish.
Make number of enchiladas desired and place in dish.
Cover with second can of a la King.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: buckeyes
directions: Knead together sugar, peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Roll into small 1-inch balls (young helpers can assist here). Refrigerate on waxed paper.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl.
Mix with hands; shape into a ball.
Garnish with pecans.

title: marshmallow goodies
directions: Freeze marshmallows.
Melt caramel candies.
Add condensed milk and oleo or butter.
Coat frozen marshmallows in caramel and roll in Rice Krispies; use a toothpick for handling.
Cool on waxed paper.
Delicious!

title: oven fried chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Meanwhile spray a broiler pan rack with nonstick spray (Pam).
Crush Special K on a piece of wax paper with a rolling pin.
Pour Special K in a plastic or paper bag and add garlic powder, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides of chicken breasts.
Place chicken breasts, one at a time, in bag with mixture and shake to cover chicken breast.
Place breasts on broiler rack.
Bake chicken breasts for 45 to 50 minutes.
When breasts are done, turn broiler on long enough for additional browning, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together oats and boiling water.
Set aside.
Cream oleo, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add oats, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, nuts, vanilla and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: mock lobster
directions: Bring 6 cups water and 1 package dry spaghetti mix to a boil. Wrap fish in cheesecloth and saturate with lemon juice.
Place fish in spaghetti mixture and boil for 5 minutes or until flaky and done.
Carefully unwrap and serve with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf with cucumber sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly. Form into loaf in shallow baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: zucchini vegetable casserole
directions: Peel vegetables, slice and place in a large baking pan.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves and seasoning.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with olive oil and cover. Bake at 400° about 30 minutes. Uncover and cook an additional 30 to 40 minutes.
Delicious!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together; add eggs and pumpkin, mixing well. Mix together dry ingredients and add alternately with water to pumpkin mixture. Pour into two well greased and floured 9 x 5 inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: * One-half pound (2 inch pieces) spaghetti is about 2 1/2 cups.

title: hott hott sauce
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator. Can add horseradish to taste. Pour over cream cheese to serve with crackers.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Make jello as usual with 1/4 cup less water.
Beat in raspberries, then sour cream.
Place in salad mold.
Chill and serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour and spices and add to mixture.
Stir in water, walnuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.
When cool, sift confectioners sugar through paper doily on top of cake.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat Bisquick and half of the garlic.
Mix in cheese.
Add milk, stirring just until moistened.
Roll dough on lightly floured board.
Cut out.
Combine butter with remaining garlic; brush on tops.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: fried catfish
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and paprika.
Dry fish thoroughly.
Coat both sides of fish with mixture.
Fry fish in hot oil over low heat, about 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 2 servings.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add whipped cream and blend.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill to set.
Add pie filling on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie or an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Pour over ice into large punch bowl.
Add rest of ingredients; chill.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Put pineapple and juice in a 9-inch casserole, greased.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour and pour over pineapple.
Brown bread in melted butter in skillet.
Put on top of fruit mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May add onions if desired.

title: red bean toss
directions: Combine beans, celery, pickle relish, onion and cheese.
Blend seasonings with mayonnaise.
Add to bean mixture and toss lightly. Spoon into 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with corn chips.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: beef steak parmigiana
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch and trim off fat.
Cut in pieces. Combine Parmesan and crumbs.
Dip meat in egg and roll in crumb mixture.
Heat oil in skillet; brown on both sides on medium heat. Transfer to shallow baking pan.
Add onion to oil.
Cook.
Stir in paste, water, salt, sugar, pepper and spices.
Bring to boil. Cook 5 minutes, scraping pan to blend in browned bits.
Pour over meat.
Reserve small amount for topping or meat.
Cover with Mozzarella and sprinkle remaining sauce on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna florentine(serves 6)
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove excess liquid.
Spread spinach evenly in a greased casserole (2-quart).
Sprinkle with onion, tuna and eggs.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour mixture evenly over eggs.
Mix melted butter and crumbs and sprinkle evenly over top of casserole.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix margarine, cheese and egg.
Toss into spaghetti.
Coat well.
Press in pie plate.
Mix 1 cup Ricotta cheese with 1 tablespoon Italian dressing, 1/2 pound ground beef and spices. Fill pie shell; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cooking.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Blend in oatmeal, wheat germ and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs, yogurt, vanilla, fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Make meringue with egg whites and sugar.
Sprinkle remainder of peanut butter mixture over meringue.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: graham squares
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mustard brine pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Have the brine in a crock jar or glass container. Add enough cucumbers so they are covered with brine.
Are ready to eat in 3 to 7 days.
Does not require refrigeration.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Rub meat with garlic, cut into strips.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Add meal; toss until coated.
Reserve flour. Heat margarine in skillet; add meat and brown.
Add onion and cook until transparent.
Add flour, consomme, mushrooms and water; cover.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover and continue cooking until mixture is slightly thickened.
Add sour cream and chives.
Serves 4.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Rinse body cavity of fish with cold water; drain and pat dry with absorbent paper.
Rub cavity with salt.
Lightly pile stuffing into fish; skewer or sew opening.
Place in shallow baking pan lined with aluminum foil or parchment.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: low-fat lentil soup
directions: Place all ingredients except rice and Parmesan in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add more broth if desired.
Serve over rice and sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add Ragu sauce.
Mix well.
Cook spaghetti.
Drain well and add to sauce.
Mix well.
Put a layer of sauce and noodles, a layer of Parmesan cheese, a layer of Cheddar cheese and a layer of Mozzarella cheese in a casserole dish.
Repeat layers again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Simmer dry beans in water with bouillon cubes and onion for 3 to 4 hours.
Add vegetable patties and tomatoes and simmer another hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about one more hour. Makes a great, almost fat-free meal!

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix 4 cups bran, flour, soda and salt.
Pour into this the rest of the bran mixed with boiling water and shortening.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
Bake as many muffins as needed in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Batter keeps 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, egg and mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients together and sour cream.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown and springs back as you touch it.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and pickle; mix lightly. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Drain vegetables; mix with celery and chicken soup.
Add 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth.
Debone and chop chicken.
Line casserole dish with chicken.
Pour vegetable and soup mixture over chicken.

title: citrus pie
directions: Whip orange
juice,
yogurt or ice cream, Cool Whip and orange extract together.
Fold mandarin oranges into mixture. Pour into pie crust and freeze until firm.
Serves 6.

title: italian stuffed rigatoni
directions: Saute onion in hot oil until soft; add tomato paste, tomatoes and water; stir well.
Add seasonings, cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
While sauce is cooking, cook rigatoni in 5-quarts of salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain; rinse with cold water; drain well.
Remove casing from sausage; break up meat and brown well.
Add bread crumbs, milk and egg; mix well.
Stuff each rigatoni with filling.
Layer sauce and rigatoni into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small bowl of mixer, beat cheese until light.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Thin frosting as you beat with juice until it is of a good spreading consistency.
Add vanilla and grated peel.
Makes enough to frost two 9-inch layers.
Increase recipe for 3 layers (8 ounces cream cheese, etc.).

title: tuna puffs
directions: Mix ingredients except for tomato, cheese and buns. Lay buns on cookie sheet. Top with mixture then lay slice of tomato then cover with cheese. Bake at 300° until cheese is bubbly and is heated throughout.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix chips, peanut butter, margarine and vanilla in large bowl. Microwave on Medium for 2 minutes and stir.
Microwave longer if not smooth.
Pour over Chex until all pieces are covered and stir to cover well.
In large bag, shake cereal and powdered sugar until mixed.
Spread on wax paper and let cool.

title: chocolate delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan put graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup oleo and 1/2 cup sugar.

title: moon rocks
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 of the coconut and mix thoroughly. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in remaining coconut.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and put in a greased casserole.
Put crushed potato chips on top.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: popcorn
directions: Put oil and popcorn in pan; heat until popcorn starts popping. Shake vigorously until corn stops popping.
Remove from pan and put into favorite popcorn bowl.
Melt butter; dribble over popcorn.
Salt.
Eat while hot; lick salt from bottom of bowl.

title: spam spread open face buns
directions: Boil eggs; slice and mash with a fork into fine pieces.
Slice Spam into very small pieces.
Mix Spam pieces, eggs and cheese with 1 teaspoon mayo.
Open the buns and spread mixture on each half.
Brown under the oven (broil) for a few minutes, until melted and slightly toasted.
Mixture will keep in the refrigerator for a week.

title: molded corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water; cool to consistency of egg whites. Whip in Miracle Whip and add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a large Pyrex dish or mold and chill overnight.

title: coconut buns
directions: Beat butter and sugar; add eggs, salt and coconut.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Bake in muffin tins at 350°.

title: pork chops with rosemary
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops.
Dip in beaten egg, then in the bread crumbs mixed with rosemary.
Brown the breaded chops in Wesson oil.
Add celery and water; cover and simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Uncover the last 5 minutes to crisp the coated chops. Makes 6 servings.

title: ham with glaze
directions: Place ham fat side up on a rack in open roasting pan.
Do not add water; do not cover.
Cook at 325°.
Allow 20 minutes per pound for a "cook before eating" ham and 15 minutes per pound for a "fully cooked" ham.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, buttermilk, eggs and Wesson oil; pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Mix nuts, brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins; sprinkle over batter and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: roman holiday
directions: Cook hamburger until done.
Drain.
Cook macaroni until half way done.
Drain. Spray dish with a non-stick spray.
Put a
layer of tomato sauce, then layer of hamburger.
Then a layer of macaroni, then layer of sliced cheese.
Repeat once more.
Bake approximately 1-1 1/2 hours until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook rice and season as directed on package.
Add soups to rice.
Do not dilute soup.
Stir until well mixed.
Add the raw, thawed broccoli.
Stir well.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Do not cover.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: easy green vegetable casserole
directions: Put vegetables in casserole.
Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour mix over vegetables.
Bake for 5 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake about an hour in 350° oven.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender. Drain and mash.
Add grated cheese and butter, saving some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Add beaten egg, milk, crushed crackers, salt and pepper.
Bake in shallow dish at 350° until set and brown, about 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.
Can add onion if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large salad bowl, layer ingredients in order given.
Do not mix.
Cover bowl tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Gently toss just before serving, mixing well.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef-mushroom casserole
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in baking dish.
Stir.
Bake at 225° for 3 1/2 hours, stirring after 2 1/2 hours.
Add red wine and mushrooms.
Stir and bake another 1/2 to 1 hour.
Serve over rice. Serves 6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour and measure with the sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir together in bowl.
Mix egg, oil and milk; add to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir until moistened; batter will be lumpy.
Add fresh, frozen or canned blueberries; stir.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.

title: fried yellow squash, eggplant, green tomatoes or zucchini
directions: Mix all dry ingredients thoroughly.
Slice vegetables 3/8 inch thick.
Dip each slice of vegetable in buttermilk and roll in dry ingredients.
Panfry in a small amount of fat (oil) or deep fry until done.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Mix together the tomato, pepper and olives.
Spread beans on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix sour cream and taco mix; spread over beans.
Sprinkle cheese over sour cream layer. On top, spread the tomato mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes, or until hot and melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes
and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain. Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add pineapple.
Stir in cubed bread.
Bake in greased covered 1 1/2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350° until lightly browned. Makes 8 servings.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour; add milk and water.
Beat egg yolks; pour in slowly, stirring constantly.
After thick, add oleo.

title: double fudge hazelnut pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa thoroughly; add to the eggs.
Add the corn syrup, cream, hazelnut liquor and melted butter.
Mix well by hand.
Add the hazelnuts and chocolate chips.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven until filling is set.
It will puff up slightly and cracks will form around edges. As pie cools, it will settle.
Texture is similar to a wet brownie.
Taste is scrumptious fudge.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour onto floured board and roll out.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Mix with onion.
Add enough cold water to dampen dough.
Next, add enough boiling water to cake like consistency.
Drop from spoon and fry in hot shortening until golden brown.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli in water and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let sit 20 minutes.
Put milk, cheese and flour in blender and blend up.
Mix with broccoli and water.
Add half and half.
Cook on medium heat until hot and thick.

title: party pizza
directions: Scramble and brown sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add sausage, green pepper and onion to cheese.
Spread on party rye bread.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
This makes enough for 2 loaves of bread.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Melt chocolate pieces over hot water.
Remove from heat; pour over marshmallows and noodles.
Toss gently until blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Chill.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: celery-chinese style
directions: Cook celery in small amount of water until crisp.
Mix together celery, water chestnuts and soup; put in 1-quart casserole dish.
Toss bread crumbs with almonds and butter and spread over top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: mexican pecan pralines
directions: Dissolve sugar, soda and Karo in milk.
Cook until light brown or, if using a candy thermometer, the soft ball stage.
Stir constantly.
It raises so use a tall pan.
Remove from heat at the soft ball stage.
Add pecans, butter and vanilla.
Beat until it begins to get thick.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: noodles
directions: Fill medium size bowl about 2/3 full of flour. Make a hole in flour, leaving some on bottom. Put all ingredients in flour and mix, stirring in flour until dough is no longer sticky. Flour a large surface and use 1/3 of dough. Roll out thin. Dry 15 to 20 minutes. Cover with a dusting of flour. Cut in half and place on top of other half. Roll up and cut in thin strips. Shake out and cook in broth. Do same with remainder of dough. Can dry and freeze.

title: surneye paeske(russian easter cheese mold)
directions: Cook orange rind in 3 to 4 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons water.
Simmer on low for 45 minutes.
Do the same with the lemon rind.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk to make white sauce.
Add salmon and seasonings.
Cool ingredients thoroughly.
Shape, dip in bread crumbs, egg, then crumbs again.
Deep fry.
Serve with Oriental sauce.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and instant pudding until well blended.
Add drained fruit salad; mix fruit and fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pan biscuits
directions: Mix milk, oil, vinegar and salt.
In a separate bowl, mix biscuit mix and cornmeal.
Add milk mixture and blend with a fork. Form into a ball and knead 10 times.
Shape into balls and flatten with your hand.
Cook in shortening in skillet over medium-low heat until browned on both sides and cooked through.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk, vanilla, raisins or chips and oats mixture.
Drop dough on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 36 cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
well.
Pour
into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: portuguese potatoes
directions: Cube and boil potatoes, leaving skin on. Place in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish or 2 smaller dishes. Mix cheese, onion, garlic, pimento and bread and sprinkle over cooked potatoes. Pour oleo over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "bigler's beefy barbecue"
directions: In frying pan (can mix both pork and beef), dice leftover meat.
Salt to taste.
Add barbecue sauce, ketchup, brown sugar and water.
Simmer until done to tenderness.
Serve on bun.

title: speedy lasagna
directions: *Can substitute with large jar of Ragu.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into an 8 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Line a 14-inch pizza pan with dough slices, overlapping and pressing them together to form a crust.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies.

title: baked slice of ham
directions: Place ham in pan just about the size of the slice.
Pour mixture over ham and bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.
Baste frequently.

title: old fashioned butter cookies(yields 6 dozen)
directions: In 3-quart mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar, and egg until light and fluffy. Beat in flour, baking powder, orange juice, and vanilla until smooth and well combined. Chill 2-3 hours or until firm enough to be rolled. Preheat oven to 400°. Roll out dough, 1/2 at a time, on well floured surface to 1/8 to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut out with cookie cutters. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake near center of oven for 6-10 minutes or until golden brown on edges. Cool on wire rack. Frost.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: In pan, combine chocolate chips and margarine.
Stir until melted.
Add condensed milk.
In bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Shape 1 tablespoon around each Kiss.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until soft and shiny.
(Will firm as they cool; do not overbake.)
Remove from sheet and cool.
Combine white chocolate and oil and drizzle over bonbons.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cantaloupe ice cream
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into freezer trays.
Cover and freeze about 1 hour or until firm around edges.
Spoon mixture into a mixing bowl and beat on medium speed with electric mixer 2 to 3 minutes or until smooth.
Return to freezer trays; cover and freeze until firm. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Heat ingredients until the mixture bubbles slightly.
Cool. Add 2 cups buttermilk and 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Mix well. Refrigerate until set.
Crushed nuts are optional.

title: mushroom broccoli casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in 1 teaspoon of canola.
Add ground turkey and cook.
Place turkey and mushrooms in a large strainer.
Wash with hot water to drain off excess fat or oil.
Combine the rest of the ingredients with mushrooms and turkey.
Put in a large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and remove from heat.
Mix all well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put small bag marshmallows over entire cake as soon as it is done.
Run under broiler until melted.
Mix these ingredients together and pour over hot marshmallows:

title: taco casserole
directions: Spread 2 cups crushed tortilla chips in casserole dish.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Add taco seasoning; stir well.
Spread over chips.
Spread chopped onion over hamburger.
Spread cheese over onion.
Cover with layer of sour cream.
Spread remaining chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: Line bottom of 8-inch square pan with slices of jalapeno peppers.
Grate Longhorn cheese; add well beaten eggs.
Pour mixture over peppers and bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Cut in pieces and serve.

title: mock guacamole
directions: Position knife blade in processor bowl.
Add asparagus. Process until smooth; transfer to mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in a paper towel lined colander; drain 1 hour.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: steak casserole
directions: Cut steak into strips and flour lightly on both sides.
Heat 2 tablespoons cooking oil in a large skillet.
Brown steak on both sides.
Pour off excess fat.
Add potatoes, mushroom soup and one can of water.
You may add more water if too thick.
Stir to keep mixture from sticking and simmer for 30 minutes over medium heat. You can also add chopped onions.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter cake icing
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter and pour melted butter over.
Slowly add milk until this thickens to spread over cooled cake.

title: dr. bird cake - or bananas and pineapple
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together. Cream sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. Add dry ingredients. Mix in bananas and pineapple. Pour into a tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done. Frost, if desired.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients well and marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour in sauce.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna until done, drain and set aside.
Brown hamburger meat; drain and mix in spaghetti sauce.
Heat together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In casserole dish, layer noodles, meat mixture, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese until last layer; don't put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Start layering with small amount of meat mixture to prevent noodles sticking to dish.
Bake in 350° oven until heated through.

title: sweet yellow bread
directions: Put yeast in water; set aside.
Combine milk, butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in eggs, vanilla, salt and yeast.
Gradually add flour.
Cover and let stand until dough doubles (approximately 1 hour).
Beat down and let rise 45 minutes more.
Turn into 2 greased bread pans and let rise 45 minutes more.
Brush tops of bread lightly with remaining egg.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: window wash
directions: Mix and use to wash those windows!

title: slushies
directions: Steep tea bags in 6 cups hot water for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze 10 hours.
Makes large amount.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: crab croquettes
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, parsley and crab meat.
Season to taste with salt.
Chill.
Shape into croquettes with hands.
Dip croquettes into egg, then in crumbs. Fry slowly in remaining butter until browned on both sides.
Serve piping hot with lemon wedges.

title: deep fried cauliflower
directions: Parboil cut up cauliflower in boiling water; let cool.
Flour cauliflower in bag with a small amount of flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dip in beaten egg and then flour.
Fry in deep oil until brown.

title: gailon's liniment
directions: Add enough D M S O to make 1 pint.
This is very good to ease pain of arthritis or any other muscular pain, but will not cure it.

title: fried squash blossoms
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, garlic salt and cumin.

title: cornstarch and water
directions: Put ingredients in bowl and mix with hands.

title: chocolate darlings(old fashioned cookie recipe; 40 years old)
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients well.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately to batter with 1/2 cup milk.
Add dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with Jell-O in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: orange creamsicle
directions: Remove Cool Whip from freezer to thaw.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add juice as is.
Add pineapple.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Add Cool Whip. Stir until well blended.
Refrigerate as a Jell-O mold.

title: french beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients, uncooked.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 to 6 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add
all	other ingredients and mix well. Pour in greased baking dish (medium size) and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: fiesta meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form meatballs.
In 2-quart pot, melt cranberry sauce and blend in salsa.
When sauce starts to boil, drop meatballs.
Continue to cook until all meatballs have cooked about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add taco seasoning and set aside until cool. Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and onion. Add cheese, olives and kidney beans. Add hamburger last. Pour dressing over and mix.

title: golden dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Place sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Heat and stir milk and shortening until shortening melts (120° to 130°).
Add to mixing bowl along with eggs and yeast mixture.
Stir in 1 cup flour at a time to form a soft dough that can be kneaded.
Knead on a lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Place in a large greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: corn bread and bacon dish
directions: Crumble the corn bread.
Add other ingredients and stir in the mayonnaise.
Chill well for several hours.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and vanilla together.
Shape potato mixture around marshmallow and roll in coconut or corn flakes. Bake at 350° until golden brown or hot throughout.
Makes about 1 dozen balls.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt.
Mix wine and mushroom soup with whisk.
Add mushrooms.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Remove chicken from pan and sprinkle with paprika.
Pour remaining sauce into saucepan.
Add sour cream and heat gently until warm.
Pour over chicken and serve with rice.

title: old time pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco. Add egg yolks one at a time. Beat well after each. Add flour and milk alternately. Add flavoring. Beat egg whites stiff and fold in. Cook 20 minutes on 350°, then 1 hour and 10 minutes on 300°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat margarine and Karo syrup in double boiler.
Add sugar next.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Pour into uncooked pastry shell.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: refrigerator-sweet dill pickles
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Boil 1 minute.
In a large nonmetallic container, combine cucumbers, onion and dill.
Pour boiling liquid on cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate 3 days before serving.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
(A gallon jar is good to use to store in refrigerator.)

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, baking soda and salt in an extra large bowl (with lid).
Add beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk, mixing well.
Store in covered container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Batter will keep in refrigerator for 6 weeks.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix and pat butter, flour and powdered sugar into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat the eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and lemon juice together for 1 minute.
Pour over the crust and bake 20 minutes more or until filling is set. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Add soda to buttermilk and let stand 1 minute.
Add sugar, Karo and butter.
Cook until forms a hard ball.
Add vanilla and nuts. Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered dish or pan.
Use a large pan.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together.
Add noodles and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper to cool.

title: 1 cup salad
directions: Layer lettuce in bottom of glass Pyrex.
Use full head of lettuce.
Next, chop 1 cup of bell pepper and sprinkle over lettuce.
Then chop 1 cup of onion and 1 cup of tomatoes and layer in order.
Then top with 1 cup of bacon bits, 1 cup of croutons and 1 cup of cheese.
Then add dressing to desired amount.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: russian borscht
directions: Cook covered the beets, carrots and onion in 2 1/2 cups boiling salted water for 20 minutes.
Add brown stock, cabbage and butter. Cook an additional 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve hot or chilled with a dollop of plain yogurt.
The soup is even better the second day.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rainbow cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream cake ingredients together.
Then divide batter into 4 separate bowls.
To each bowl add enough color for batter to be bright and vivid - (4 different colors).
Layer into bundt pan - try not to layer same color on same color.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients gradually to the creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Reserve remaining M&M's for decorating.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with reserved candies. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Press this mixture into a greased or floured square or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix by adding ingredients one at a time.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Put this pan into another pan full of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: In
saucepan combine sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook to hard ball stage, (may use candy thermometer), stirring only until sugar dissolves.
Meanwhile, beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually
pour
syrup
over
egg whites and beat at high speed with
mixer
about	2
minutes.
Add
vanilla and nuts and beat until candy holds its shape, 4 or 5 minutes.
Quickly drop from teaspoon
on
waxed
paper.
Yield: 40 pieces.
Use light brown sugar for caramel divinity.

title: very easy no crust apple pie
directions: Fill the pie pan 3/4 full with the apples.
In a separate bowl, mix together all the other ingredients.
Spread over the top of the apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until the top is golden brown.

title: corn and broccoli bake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter; reserve 1/2 cup for topping. Combine broccoli, corn and remaining crumbs in a bowl.
Stir until blended.
Place mixture in a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cream
butter.	Add sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil and
cook
three minutes.
Remove from range and allow to cool. Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in casserole pan.
Pepper to taste. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 400° oven.

title: irish apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Mix separately all dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts
and apples.
Mix thoroughly with wooden spoon.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured.
Sprinkle butterscotch drops on top. Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Let set 10 minutes. Cut in squares to serve.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Cool. Add onions, cucumbers, lemon juice, sugar, sour cream and mayonnaise. Put all this in a blender. Pour in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Let set.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Saute meat and onions.
Add garlic salt, soups, taco sauce, green chilies and tomato paste; mix well.
Layer in 3-quart casserole with tortillas and cheese.
Cover and cook at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover; add lots of cheese and return to oven to melt.

title: low country cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend 1 minute.
Makes 6 cups.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and vegetables in large bowl.
Combine olive oil and remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake well. Pour on vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: taco taters
directions: Place fries in a well greased cookie sheet.
Spray with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Bake according to package directions.
Serve immediately.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: english muffins in a loaf
directions: Dissolve the sugar in warm water; add yeast and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir well.
Combine milk and salt in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until lukewarm only.
Add to dissolved yeast.
Add 3 cups flour, combined with baking soda.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in enough of remaining 3 cups flour to make a stiff batter.
Divide in half and press into 2 loaf pans (greased and sprinkled with cornmeal).
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal and cover.
Let rise in warm place 45 minutes or until center of loaf is about 1 1/2 inches above edge of pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
To serve, slice and toast.
Spread with butter and jam if desired.

title: cheesy broccoli and chicken
directions: Cut chicken in chunks and cook in sprayed skillet until done. Stir in broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir in macaroni.
Reduce heat to medium-low and cook until macaroni is done.
Add cheese and broccoli until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping. Combine remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg. Pour into pan.
Combine pie mix, 2 eggs and milk.
(Tip:
When using 1 pound can solid packed pumpkin, add 2 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice and 1/4 cup firmly packed brown sugar.)
Place filling over base.
Combine reserved cake mix and 1/4 cup sugar. Sprinkle topping over filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and cut into squares.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into an oblong baking dish, coated with vegetable spray.
Pour margarine over top of mixture and bake at 425° for 25 minutes until brown.

title: old fashion party cooler
directions: Combine chilled grapefruit juice and sugar; chill.
Just before serving, add chilled lemon soda.
Pour in glasses and top with small scoop of lime sherbet.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: After washing broccoli and cutting up into small florets, cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble bacon into broccoli you've placed in a fairly large bowl to allow for mixing.
Add raisins.
Don't skimp. They really add to the flavor.
Thoroughly mix in mayo.
Sprinkle with sugar and mix again.
Tastes best if made ahead a couple of hours.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding milk to mix only to make a dipping consistency.
Chill before serving.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except rice in skillet.
Cook, uncovered, until meat is cooked.
Add rice and mix well.

title: dill sandwiches
directions: Trim crust off bread.
Mix onion, cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Cut each pickle into even strips (usually 6).
Spread cream cheese mixture over slice of bread.
Place strip of pickle in middle of bread and roll up.
Refrigerate rolls overnight. Before serving, slice each roll with an electric knife into approximately 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Serves 60.

title: beef and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Pour boiling water over rice.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Drain; place rice in casserole dish. Add soups and seasonings.
Mix gently.
Slice and saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix into rice.
Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter butter until limp.
Mix into rice.
Brown meat; add to rice and mix.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
May be refrigerated up to 24 hours before baking. Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in saucepan; mix well.
Cook using package directions.
Add cake mix gradually, stirring constantly.
Batter will be very stiff.
Spread evenly in greased and floured 10 x 15-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Press lightly into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool in pan.
Yields 24 servings.

title: apple-raisin muffins
directions: Toss apples with sugar and walnuts; set aside.
Add oil and vanilla to beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir in raisins and currants.
Add dry ingredient mixture to egg mixture. Add apples; stir until combined.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until muffins spring back when touched and pull away from side of tin.

title: rolls
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: In bowl or blender, combine all ingredients, except nutmeg. Mix until frothy.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sour milk griddle cakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add to milk and egg.

title: never fail chicken parmigiana
directions: Beat eggs. Mix garlic, salt and pepper to bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Fry in pan until done (olive oil is best).
In large baking dish, place chicken, then tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, then Mozzarella.
Layer a little Parmesan on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: reeses no cook fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate bits.
Press into a 9 x 14-inch pan, ungreased.
Melt chocolate bits and smooth over top.

title: very best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake on top oven rack at 325° for 10 minutes for chewy cookies.
(May want to add a tablespoon or so more flour and bake a bit longer.)

title: children's pizza bread pronto
directions: Spread butter over cut sides of rolls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Broil 4 inches from heat until lightly browned. Spread several tablespoons over sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with oregano.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve hot. Makes 8 servings.

title: tortellini soup stew
directions: Combine tomatoes, sausage (uncooked), tomato sauce, beef stock, onion, garlic, carrots, basil and oregano in a large pot. Simmer 30 minutes.
Do not boil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer another hour.
Add tortellini last.
Serves 10.

title: pull-away coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Line bottom of pan with nuts.
Arrange frozen rolls (I cut into half) around pan on top of nuts.
Shake cinnamon on top.
Pour instant Jell-O (dry) on top of rolls.
Melt oleo and brown sugar together and pour evenly over top.
Cover and let rise (sit out) overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: neapolitan casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling salted water until tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add flour; mix well.
Add mushroom soup and mushrooms; set aside, but keep warm.
Take 2 1/2 cups of broth from cooking chicken and use to cook rice by directions on box.
In a casserole dish, layer mushroom mixture, chicken and wild rice.
Alternate until all is used.
Put slices of cheese on top.
Put in oven long enough for cheese to melt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, butter and milk. Cook to soft ball stage (234° to 240°). Stir in cornstarch dissolved in small amount of water. Remove from heat. Beat well. Add vanilla and peanut butter. Beat until smooth. Add nuts. Stir until blended. Pour into buttered square pan. Cool and slice.
Also great as an icing for Peanut Butter Cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in bowl. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until sugar dissolves; pour over broccoli and mix.

title: parsley and parmesan baked chicken
directions: Remove chicken skin.
Pour salad dressing into 13
x 9 x 2-inch
baking pan.
Add chicken, turning to
coat	all
sides. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Drain and reserve
dressing.	Combine all ingredients.
Dip chicken into egg mixture,
then	into
crumb mixture.
Return coated mixture to baking pan.
Spoon remaining dressing over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 40
to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift half of the sugar with the flour 4 times. Beat egg whites to a foam. Add cream of tartar and salt; beat until it holds up in peaks. Add remainder of sugar, a little at a time, beating it in. Add flavoring. Fold in the flour mixture slowly, using a down and up motion. Pour into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop and cook celery and onion in oleo. Mix with other ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nut squares
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread into greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mom's perfect spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage, drain.
Add to large pot with remaining ingredients.
You may add more or less depending on your taste.
Mix well and let simmer for one hour, stirring occasionally.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: In heavy skillet combine all of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir constantly until all liquids have evaporated and the walnuts are coated with sugar.
Spread on a cookie sheet, separating the nuts and allowing them to cool.

title: mini cheesecake
directions: Place foil liners in muffin tin. Put vanilla wafer in each. Mix all ingredients well. Pour over wafers 3/4 way full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool. Top with fruit or chocolate.

title: applesauce loaf bread
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the applesauce. Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour into greased bread pans, 8 x 10 x 3-inches. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: self-frosting angel cake
directions: Beat
egg
whites
(room temperature) until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt. Beat until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, beating mixture until stiff peaks form.
Sprinkle flour over egg white mixture. Fold in carefully.	Gently	fold
in flavorings.
Pour batter into ungreased
9-inch
square pan. Sprinkle coconut over top. Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes. Cool in pan about 40 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and cut into squares.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil, together and sprinkle on tomato.
Add 1 teaspoon oil to each and broil.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Makes 18 small muffins.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease a casserole
dish.
Place
a layer of 1/2 of the asparagus, 1 egg, 1/2
of
the soup, 3 crumbled crackers and 3 pats oleo.	Then layer
of the asparagus, 1 egg, 3 crackers, 3 pats oleo
and
remainder of soup.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Great!

title: white bark candy
directions: Melt white bark over double boiler. Add peanut butter and rest of ingredients in order. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: beer ball appetizers
directions: Season hamburger with salt and pepper as you like and shape into bite size balls.
Brown on a cookie sheet at 350°.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add meatballs and simmer 3 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken; line bottom of 9 x 13 casserole. Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken. Melt butter; mix crumbled crackers and poppy seed. Spread over top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of butter. Add soup, Cheez Whiz, rice and drained broccoli.
Bake in large casserole dish for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broiled fish a l'orange
directions: Arrange fish on rack in broiler pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush lightly over fish.
Place under hot broiler for 10 minutes, basting with remaining sauce.

title: grasshopper cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions and cool.
Heat chocolate fudge and coat cake and cool.
Take container of Cool Whip and add creme de menthe and combine.
Frost cake.

title: rolls (white)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough flour to pull dough away from side.
Leave in warm place to double in size.
Form rolls, 2 ounces each, then let rise double again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured round pans or a 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 45 minutes, depending on the size pan used, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove and cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage or bacon and drain.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole and put bread cubes in bottom of casserole.
Crumble sausage or bacon over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and salt together and pour over meat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or freeze.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(Takes about an hour whether frozen or not.)
Serves 8.

title: crown roast of pork
directions: *A 5-pound roast is about 10 to 12 chops, serving 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring 1 cup water to a boil. Mix with jello. Add remaining water. Refrigerate until it begins to gel. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate. Great with ham or turkey.

title: whipped cheese pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup sugar slowly and keep beating until stiff.
In separate bowl, beat cheese until smooth; add yolks.
Beat well.
Mix flour, salt and remaining sugar; add to mixture with vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top generously with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: shrimp curry or creole
directions: Chop bell pepper, onions, pimentos and garlic; brown in 1/4 cup oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Add 1 teaspoon cornstarch dissolved in 1/2 cup dry wine. Cook for 3 minutes. To make curry, add 2 teaspoons curry powder.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat all together. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine; press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: raspberry-cranberry jello salad
