directions: In large bowl, mix jello and boiling water (1 cup at a time), about 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Mash cranberry sauce with fork and mix into jello.
Place in refrigerator to cool and set while peeling, coring and cutting apples into small cubes. Cut celery stalks into small pieces.
Stir apples and celery in jello-cranberry mixture.
Return to refrigerator to set, about 4 hours.

title: popovers
directions: Heat oven to 425° (hot).
Heavily grease 6 deep custard cups. Beat eggs slightly and add milk, Wondra flour and salt.
Stir with fork just until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Fill greased custard cups 1/2 full.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with honey butter. Mix honey in butter and whip together; chill.

title: broasted potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut each in half or quarters; do not peel. Brush cut edges with melted butter or oleo.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 425° until they turn golden brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots in rounds and boil in salted water for 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Put soup, oil, vinegar and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Layer carrots, onions and peppers in baking dish.
Pour hot soup mixture over them.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pink punch
directions: Combine the sugar and water; stir until dissolved (clear). Boil for 10 minutes.
Let cool for 30 minutes.
Mix in the pineapple and orange and lemon juices.
Add wine and chill at least 2 hours.
At serving time, pour over ice in a punch bowl. Add cherries, stirring lightly.
Taste.
If too tart, add sugar. If too sweet, add more wine or club soda.

title: microwave chocolate nut bark
directions: To melt chocolate pieces:
Put in dish and cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Medium (5) for about 4 to 6 minutes, or until melted.
Do not microwave too long.

title: pecan balls - christmas cookie(snowballs)
directions: Cream butter and add rest of ingredients.
Flour your hands and roll into bite size balls, about 1-inch around.
Spray a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Mix ingredients together well and cover. Let set in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: easy pizzaburgers
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain.
Add soup, sharp cheese, oregano and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spread mixture on buns.
Place Mozzarella cheese on top of mixture.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: hot antipasto
directions: Drain all ingredients; mix all together. Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs; beat hard until light.
Add bananas.
Stir in flour until mixture is smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes until done.
Cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Core cabbage and put in boiling water.
As leaves become wilted, peel them off and place on paper towels to dry.
Trim out center vein of each leaf.
Saute onion and garlic in butter.
Add meat, rice, seasonings and stir together.
Simmer 20 minutes. Place a tablespoon of this filling on each cabbage leaf and roll up leaf.
Place in a pot in layers.
Cover filled cabbage leaves 2/3 with water.
Stir together tomato paste, sour cream and sauerkraut.
Spoon this over top.
Cover and cook on simmer for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Take meat off bones; save the broth.
Saute chopped vegetables in margarine or chicken broth.
Cook noodles. Mix with vegetables and chicken.
Layer mixture with cheese in a casserole dish.
Mix soup with 2 to 3 cups chicken broth and pour over the dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 8.

title: ziti and cheese bake
directions: Cook pasta until done; drain.
Combine pasta with eggs, skim milk, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and pepper.
Coat a 1-quart baking dish with cooking spray; put combined ingredients in dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and milk. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
Cover and chill. Garnish as desired.

title: mexican salad
directions: As you prepare, layer ingredients in bowl and drizzle with salad dressing.
Before serving, crush one bag of Fritos or Doritos and toss with salad.
Serves 8.

title: poor man's cake(eggless and milkless)
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Let stand until cool.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until it tests done (toothpick inserted comes out clean).
Turn out on cooling rack.
When cool, dust with confectioners sugar, use cream cheese frosting or serve plain.

title: apple butter
directions: Place apples and juice in a microproof bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Carefully remove wrap and stir in remaining ingredients.
Return to microwave and cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring every 2 to 3 minutes.
Transfer mixture to a blender and process until smooth.
Store in airtight jars in the refrigerator.

title: crackling bread
directions: Mix and sift together the dry ingredients; add milk and stir in cracklings.
Form with hands into oblong cakes and place on greased baking pans.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
(I make mine in iron skillet sometimes.)

title: pillsbury corn dog twists
directions: Securely
insert
a
wooden
stick
into
each hot dog. Unroll dough into one long sheet and seal center perforations. Separate dough into 8 long strips (2 twists each).
Wrap each long
strip around a hot dog.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet with
ends
of dough
tucked under hot dog.
Brush dough with margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12
to 16 minutes or until cornbread twists are a light golden brown.
Makes 8 corn dog twists.

title: italian broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, omitting salt. Combine eggs and undiluted soup. Mix well.
Stir in broccoli and tomatoes.
Spoon mixture into greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: souper tuna lamaze
directions: Dressing:
Combine soup, mayonnaise, pickle relish, lemon juice, onion and mustard.

title: hot and spicy chicken drummies
directions: Cut off tips (last joint of wing).
Divide each wing in half. Place
in
a
single layer in flat baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, turning once.

title: grilled hot dogs and toppings
directions: Grill franks over medium coals.
Prepare toppings.
Serve franks with desired toppings.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream brown sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: banana pudding
directions: Cook until done.
Cool.
Put in 3 tablespoons Cool Whip.
Place vanilla wafers on bottom, then add pudding.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up, then place wafers on top.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Put first 8 ingredients into saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes and cool.
Add 2 cups flour into which has been sifted 1/2 teaspoon baking powder.
Add soda dissolved in small amount of hot water. May add nuts.
Pour into 2 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: finger salad
directions: Roll crescent rolls flat on large cookie sheet.
Separate rolls to fit.
Bake according to package directions or until golden brown. Let cool.
Mix ingredients and spread on rolls. Layer veggies on rolls.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine all dry ingredients except sugars and sift.
Combine and cream the shortening, sugars, molasses and egg.
Combine two mixtures.
Chill until firm and easily handled.

title: steak florentine
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil 5 to 6-inches from heat unit for 5 minutes on each side.
Saute garlic, remove from heat and add rest of ingredients.
Put over steak.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Peel carrots and potatoes.
Cut potatoes in eighths.
Cook potatoes and carrots in pot together until almost done.
Add just enough water to cover.
Brown hamburger in frypan.
Put hamburger with potatoes and carrots.
Add juice and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place cheese and ham slices on chicken; fold over and fasten with toothpicks.
Mix flour and paprika; coat chicken.
Cook chicken over medium heat in butter until brown on all sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove toothpicks.
Blend cream and cornstarch. Remove chicken from skillet.
Add cream mixture to pan and stir until thickened.
Serve over chicken.

title: ham or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in medium to large saucepan and add flour.
Stir well until blended.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until thick.
Add seasonings, turkey or ham, spaghetti, mushrooms and cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes or use hash browns.
Finely chop onions.
Add salt, pepper, celery salt and bacon or butter.
Cover with quart of water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Blend flour with milk; add to the hot soup.
Stir until it comes to a boil.
Cook for a few minutes.
Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning sauce following directions on back of package.
Add kidney beans.
Set meat mixture aside; use at room temperature.

title: eggplant supreme
directions: Brown onion and pepper slowly in olive oil.
Peel eggplant and tomatoes; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Add to onion and pepper; sprinkle seasonings.
Mix. Spoon about 1/3 mixture into 2-quart baking dish. Top with 1/2 rice.
Repeat layers; top with eggplant.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes, or until eggplant is tender.
Remove; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes, uncovered, or until cheese has melted.
Serves 6.

title: heath toffee bar coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, margarine and both sugars.
Set aside 1/2 cup of this mixture.
To the remainder add the buttermilk, soda, egg, vanilla and 1/2 c. of chopped Heath bars.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 X 12 baking pan.
Mix remaining 1/2 c. Heath bars with chopped pecans and add to set-aside mixture.
Sprinkle evenly over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over this.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over these two. Pour the melted oleo over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain.
Pour pasta in large bowl.
Drain tomatoes and pour over pasta.
Add chopped cucumber and onion.
Drain olives and pour into bowl.
Pour bottle of Italian dressing (well shook) over mixiure and stir.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into the creamed mixture. Fold in rhubarb and nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Wrap and serve the following day for the best flavor.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Measure dry ingredients; mix together. Mix egg, milk and oil together, then add to dry ingredients until moist.
Do not beat.
Add cheese and ham.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins, filling 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan immediately.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine above ingredients except for chips and cheese. Top with cheese and chip mixture. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.

title: no sugar, no salt pickles
directions: Pack pickles in jars.
Add saccharin, vinegar and boiling water.
Seal.
Process 10 minutes.
Store 4 weeks before eating.

title: blond brownies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and set aside.
Add brown sugar to melted butter and cool slightly.
(If vegetable shortening is used, add 1 tablespoon hot water.)
Add 1 beaten egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add flour mixture a small amount at a time.
Mix well after each addition. Spread into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 bag of chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 24 hours.

title: nacho-chili dip
directions: Heat chili.
Add cheese and stir well.	Serve warm with corn chips.
Add dash of Tabasco, if desired.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Saute onions in oil; add ground chuck and brown well.
Add tomatoes, juice, rice, chili powder, salt, pepper, sugar and Worcestershire.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove tops and seed from peppers; parboil 5 minutes.
Drain.
Stuff peppers with rice mixture.
Place in greased baking dish; add small amount of water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until very light.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between each addition.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter, food coloring, marshmallows and vanilla in double boiler.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper and shape into the form of a wreath and dot with small red hots.

title: fruity oat-bran muffins
directions: Combine oat bran, oats, flour(s), sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl mix remaining ingredients.
Combine with dry ingredients; do not overmix.
Coat two 12-muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray or line with muffin cups.
Fill each 2/3 full with muffin mixture. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: mother-in-law punch
directions: Mix juices and water together.
Refrigerate until used.
Stir well and add chilled ginger ale before serving.
Makes about 1 1/2 gallons of punch.
(This is not a very sweet punch.)

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, crumbled bacon and onions; set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes or chips or buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: quick pepper steak
directions: Range Top:
Mix cornstarch, 2 tablespoons water, soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil and pepper in a bowl; stir in beef.
Cover and let stand at least 15 minutes to marinate.
Heat remaining oil in skillet.
Add beef, green peppers and garlic; cook and stir until meat is brown and peppers are crisp-tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups hot water; cook and stir to loosen brown particles and bring mixture to a boil.
Stir in rice; simmer 5 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and dry jello together. Add oil, eggs and 1 cup pureed strawberries. Pour into greased floured 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes or until done. While still warm, put holes all over cake and pour remaining pureed strawberries over top. Cool. Ice with strawberry cream frosting.

title: date crunch
directions: Combine the first five ingredients in frying pan and place on low heat.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour over Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Roll in small balls and roll each in coconut.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain very well.
Squeeze until dry.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
You can also add a can of crabmeat.
Keeps well for several days.

title: guacamole(serves 4)
directions: Mash avocados.
Add a little sour cream and stir.
Add diced tomatoes, olives and Tabasco to taste.
Add lime and stir.

title: pork barbecues
directions: Roast pork, slice and set aside.

title: company casserole
directions: Boil vegetables until tender; drain. Add soup, milk, cheese, onion and ham. Pour into casserole pan; top with croutons. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Make crushed pineapple into ice cubes the night before.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl with the strawberries and pineapple cubes.

title: chocolate almond coconut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press in a 9-inch greased pan.
Combine coconut and 3/4 cup condensed milk and spread over crust. Sprinkle with almonds evenly.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
While baking, mix 1/2 cup of condensed milk and chocolate chips together and heat over low heat until melted.
Stir in vanilla; spread over warm bars and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In double boiler, cook 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and cold water until thick.
Add egg yolks with cooked mixture.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice and margarine.
Spoon hot filling into baked pie shell.

title: ham quiche
directions: Beat eggs. Add cornstarch to milk and mix all ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until center is firm. Use food processor for the ham, peppers and onion.

title: trout with almonds
directions: Heat 6 tablespoons of butter in a frying pan; add the almonds and heat well.
Add the lemon juice.
Sift the flour onto a sheet of waxed paper; salt it lightly and dredge the fish in it so that they each have a thin coating of flour.
Heat 6 tablespoons of butter in a large frying pan and when very hot, add 4 trout. Shake the pan a little as they cook to prevent sticking.
Cook about 5 minutes on each side and remove to a hot platter.

Add the remaining 6 tablespoons butter to the pan for the next batch. When all are cooked and arranged on the platter, pour the almond mixture over them and garnish with lemon wedges, dipped in finely chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: vienna squares
directions: Make pastry by blending flour, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and egg yolks with fingers.
Pat into buttered cookie sheet; prick with fork.
Bake until golden, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread with jam.
Beat egg whites stiff, gradually adding remaining sugar; beat.
Fold in nuts.
Spread meringue over jam. Bake for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender (canned potatoes can be used as well).
Remove skin and beat potatoes until fluffy.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Form ball over marshmallow and roll in shredded coconut or crushed cornflakes and bake in moderate oven until golden brown.
Best when served chilled.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and gradually add sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Add almond extract.
Pour a layer of batter (enough to cover bottom of pan) in pan and spoon in cranberry sauce.
(Mix cranberries thoroughly before.)
Add remaining batter.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Whip the cream and whip egg whites; set aside.
Mix sugar and egg yolks; beat (electric mixer) until smooth.
Add milk and egg nog mix; stir well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: banana fudge-walnut brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of an 8-inch square pan.

title: golf ball candy
directions: Mix together and form a ball.
Melt a 12 ounce package of butterscotch morsels and 1/2 square paraffin wax.
Dip the balls into mixture.

title: woo's blue-plate special meat loaf(in honor of stallion, "clifton boy")
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, veal and pork lightly with fork; set aside.
In saute pan, heat bacon fat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until soft and translucent.
Add parsley, salt, thyme, sage and pepper.
Stir in wine (beef broth if one prefers). Cook over high heat, stirring, until wine is nearly evaporated. Remove from heat and let cool.

title: *turta - a macedonian shortbread(traditionally baked on march 1)
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add the butter, margarine, oil, eggs and milk and mix well.
Knead for 10 minutes. Form into 2 rounds.
Press dough with palms of hands to flatten to approximately 1 1/2-inches.
Score the top crisscross.
Place dough on a floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown. Cool on rack.

title: apple pie pizza
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 teaspoon salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add cheese.
Sprinkle water on top and shape into ball.
Roll into 15-inch circle on floured surface. Place on baking sheet. Turn up edge to form rim or place in 13-inch pizza pan.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Measure first 3 ingredients into sifter; set aside.
Plump raisins in boiling water; drain well and set aside with nuts. Gradually beat sugar into butter.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add raisins and nuts.
Sift in 1/2 of flour mixture; stir just until moistened and fairly smooth.
Add undrained pineapple, then stir in rest of flour mixture.
Gently spoon heavy batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with topping mixture.

title: bran and oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° to 330° for 20 minutes in lightly greased muffin tins.

title: broccoli soup with ginger
directions: Combine the onion, broccoli and 1/2 cup broth in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 6 to 9 minutes, or until the broccoli is tender, stirring once.
Pour the mixture into the bowl of a food processor or blender and finely chop. Return the mixture to the casserole.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on High for 2 to 6 minutes, or until just heated through, but not boiling.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of melted butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 package of dry dressing mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with celery sticks and prepared dressing mix as dip.

title: apple betty
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder salt and egg until crumbly. Pour mixture over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 1/3 cup melted butter over all.
Do not cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Brown chops on both sides in large heavy skillet.
Top with sliced tomato, slice of onion and slice of green pepper.
One slice of each on pork chops.
Add the uncooked rice, beef cubes, salt and pepper.
Add 3 cups water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
May have to add more as it cooks.

title: oreo ice cream delight
directions: Crumble cookies in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread half the cookies in pan.
Layer with 1/2 the ice cream, 1/2 nuts and 1/2 chocolate syrup or hot fudge.
Repeat layers.
Top with whipped cream and cherries.
Freeze until set and slightly firm. Serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix juice and ginger ale.
Add sherbet just before serving.

title: cafe hot chocolate
directions: Brew coffee and pour into coffee cups or mugs, add syrup and whipped cream or creamer. May also garnish with chocolate chips.

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: In medium pan, cook onion in butter until soft, approximately 5 minutes.
Stir in flour; cook 2 minutes.
Slowly add water and chicken bouillon, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup of the sauce, turkey, 1 cup of cheese, chilies, pimiento and chili powder.
Mix well; set aside.
Fry tortillas in oil just long enough to soften, about 30 seconds per side.
Drain on paper. Spoon about 1/4 cup turkey mixture on each tortilla; roll up. Arrange in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over enchiladas; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise.
Then add mayonnaise until desired consistency is reached.
Refrigerate.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook 1 hour in a 350° oven or 3-6 hours in a crockpot.

title: betty's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly combine beef, sausage and crushed crackers.
Beat egg.
Add to tomato sauce, then add parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Pour into meat mixture and mix together well.
Put in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a covered 3 quart saucepan cook sliced onions in butter until tender, about 20 minutes.
Add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and dash of pepper.
Bring to boiling.

title: chocolate lover's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer, except for chocolate chips and nuts, until well blended or for 2 minutes.
Stir in some nuts and all of the chocolate chips.
Put 1/2 cup of the nuts on the bottom of the 9 x 13-inch pan before pouring in the batter. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: flour tortilla cobbler
directions: Wrap pie filling in tortillas and place in a greased baking dish.
Mix water and sugar together; pour over rolled tortillas, then drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients except pie crust. Do not beat. Place in pie shell and freeze.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: In skillet, saute onion and brown hamburger meat.
In bowl, combine jalapenos, 1/4 cup enchilada sauce, 1/2 can of cream of cheese soup and 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup.
In each tortilla, put about 3 tablespoons of mixture in bowl, then roll up tortillas.
Place them beside one another in casserole dish.
Then combine 1/4 cup enchilada sauce, 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can cream of cheese soup.
Spread this over enchiladas. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: maple carrots
directions: Place peeled carrots in a saucepan with about an inch of water plus salt and sugar.
Cover and cook 10 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Remove carrots from the pan and keep warm.
Cook carrot water until it is reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Add syrup, butter and mustard.
Cook until a heavy syrup is formed, about 7 minutes.
Add carrots and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add spices and egg yolks. Beat well. Sift together flour, salt and soda. Add alternately with sour cream. Lastly fold in beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix and beat.
Sift flour, soda and mace together.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Beat. Add vanilla.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding melted butter last.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden brown sugar topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Over low heat cook, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved and butter is melted.
Use to top yeast breads, rolls, coffee cakes or pound cakes.
Perfect for candied sweet potatoes or ice cream.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Combine chocolate pieces, butter and water.
Cook in microwave oven 4 minutes, stirring several times.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Cook in microwave oven an additional 30 to 60 seconds until smooth and thickened.
Serve over ice cream, pound cake or pudding.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: newport's sugar cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients, then add dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 1 hour, then roll out and cut (with cookie cutter, if desired).
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Bakes real quick. Delicious!!

title: hopping john
directions: Cook the peas and saute the onion and peppers and mix.
Add all the ingredients and serve hot.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Pour over hot cake as soon as it comes from the oven.
Cool and serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: great enchiladas
directions: Saute onion.
Add chicken, olives, chiles and 1/2 can enchilada sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll mixture up in tortillas.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with remaining sauce and cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with sour cream and more sliced olives.

title: baked green beans
directions: Place green beans in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the brown sugar and catsup; pour over beans.
Fry bacon until crisp; crumble over top of beans.
Pour off half of bacon grease; brown onion slightly in remaining grease.
Pour onion over top of beans; mix well.
Bake at 200° or 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: diabetic banana cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Add oil and sweetener; mix well until light.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned ginger bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch round baking pan.
In bowl of a food processor, combine flour, sugar, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, pepper, salt, baking soda and cocoa.
Pulse on and off 2 or 3 times to blend.
Add the remaining ingredients and pulse on and off 4 or 5 times or until flour just disappears.
Do not overmix.
(Ingredients can be mixed by hand.)
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Smooth top with rubber spatula.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: layered peach dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pecan crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft and smooth; add sugar and flavorings and blend until smooth.
Stir in flour gradually, finally stir in nuts.
Shape in small, crescent-shaped rolls, using about 1 teaspoon for each one.
Place on a buttered cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Saute cubed chicken breasts with vegetable oil, garlic powder and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
When chicken is halfway cooked, add cubed carrots.
When carrot is medium cooked, add cooked rice and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
When needed, add salt for taste or more soy sauce.
After mixing everything, turn the heat to low.
Cover the wok or frying pan and let it cook for another 3 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Pour warm water with baking soda over dates.
Set aside.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add date mixture, flour, nuts and cherries.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check with knife; if moist, not drippy, take out of oven.
If too moist, bake for 10 more minutes.

title: d.j air biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: You may use squash instead of pumpkin.

title: kielbasa kraut potato bake
directions: Add sauerkraut to kielbasa until browned. Place in baking dish. Top with mashed potatoes and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: easy no boil lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a saucepan brown beef.
Drain fat. Add spaghetti sauce and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cola cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour and set aside.
Bring butter, cocoa and cola to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add along with eggs and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Add marshmallows.
Pour into greased 14 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 35 (2-inch) squares.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift flour, soda and nutmeg.
Add to mixture, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Dredge nuts and fruit in 1/2 cup flour.
Add to batter; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Yield: 7 dozen.

title: deer steaks
directions: Put desired number of steaks in a glass bowl. Pour dressing over meat. Cover with plastic wrap. Marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning steaks several times.
Remove from dressing and fry a few at a time in vegetable oil, only a few minutes on each side.

title: danish layer cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff, adding sugar a little at a time while beating.
Beat egg yolks until stiff, adding 1/2 cup sugar a little at a time.
Fold vanilla into egg whites.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; fold into egg mixture.
Pour into two 8 x 8-inch pans.
(Do not grease.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cold, slice each layer so you will have 4 layers.
Put pudding between 2 layers and jam on one.
Then put pudding over all of the cake.
This can be done the day before.
Keep in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, cover with whipped cream.
(Use thread or sharp knife to divide layers.)

title: kat's casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter and drain. Add garlic juice and simmer 20 minutes. Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt and pepper to meat and mix. Cook noodles and drain. Mix cream cheese and sour cream and add onions.

title: rice surprise
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir thoroughly.
Bake for 15 more minutes.
Serve with round steak, or if you choose, serve the steak in the casserole.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve on crackers or toasted rye bread.

title: applesauce
directions: Wash apples and cut into quarters.
Place in saucepan and partly cover them with water.
New apples require very little water.
Stew the apples until tender.
Put them through a strainer or ricer.
Return the strained apples to the saucepan.
Add enough sugar to make them palatable.
Boil them for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
(If served hot, add 1 teaspoon of butter; if served cold, add 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.)
If applesauce is to be served with pork, add 1 to 2 teaspoons horseradish.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish; crush soda crackers and place in dish. Saute onions in margarine; place over crackers and pour mushroom soup over top.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over onion mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread cheese over top and cover with more crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients, roll in small balls.
Brown in 400° oven about 5 minutes.
These are good for freezing.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, chili powder, cumin and red pepper in large bowl.
Mix until blended; stir in salsa.
Spread onto 10-inch serving platter lined with lettuce.
Top with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Makes 10 appetizer servings.
